{"term": "1980", "caseName": "Wood v. Georgia", "caseLink": "https://www.oyez.org/cases/1980/79-6027", "caseTranscripts": [{"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - November 04, 1980", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/burger6/oral_argument_audio/18220", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "We'll wait for the noise to subside, counsel.", "start": 0, "stop": 65.208, "duration": 65.21, "cleanText": [["we", "will", "wait", "for", "the", "noise", "to", "subside", "counsel"]]}, {"text": "We'll wait for a moment or two, here.", "start": 65.208, "stop": 80.468, "duration": 15.26, "cleanText": [["we", "will", "wait", "for", "a", "moment", "or", "two", "here"]]}, {"text": "I think you may proceed whenever you are ready, now, Mr. Zell.", "start": 80.468, "stop": 84.27, "duration": 3.8, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "you", "may", "proceed", "whenever", "you", "be", "ready", "now", "mr", "zell"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court:", "start": 84.27, "stop": 87.039, "duration": 2.77, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "This case involves an issue that was left open in Tate v. Short, and that is, may a trial judge revoke the probation of the probationer or offender if he does not have the funds to make the monthly payments.", "start": 87.039, "stop": 108.119, "duration": 21.08, "cleanText": [["this", "case", "involve", "an", "issue", "that", "be", "leave", "open", "in", "tate", "v", "short", "and", "that", "be", "may", "a", "trial", "judge", "revoke", "the", "probation", "of", "the", "probationer", "or", "offender", "if", "he", "do", "not", "have", "the", "fund", "to", "make", "the", "monthly", "payment"]]}, {"text": "The facts in this case are, I think, rather clear.", "start": 108.119, "stop": 113.089, "duration": 4.97, "cleanText": [["the", "fact", "in", "this", "case", "be", "i", "think", "rather", "clear"]]}, {"text": "There are three probationers, of course; three Petitioners in this Court.", "start": 113.089, "stop": 118.407, "duration": 5.32, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "three", "probationer", "of", "course", "three", "petitioner", "in", "this", "court"]]}, {"text": "Raymond Wood, Edna Allen, and James Tante.", "start": 118.407, "stop": 122.961, "duration": 4.55, "cleanText": [["raymond", "wood", "edna", "allen", "and", "james", "tante"]]}, {"text": "They were convicted several years ago of distributing obscene materials.", "start": 122.961, "stop": 128.782, "duration": 5.82, "cleanText": [["they", "we", "be", "convict", "several", "year", "ago", "of", "distribute", "obscene", "material"]]}, {"text": "The records show that Mr. Wood was a clerk in a bookstore... no dispute about that... Ms. Allen was a projectionist in a theater, and Mr. Tante was the projectionist in that theater.", "start": 128.782, "stop": 144.624, "duration": 15.84, "cleanText": [["the", "record", "show", "that", "mr", "wood", "be", "a", "clerk", "in", "a", "bookstore", "no", "dispute", "about", "that", "ms", "allen", "be", "a", "projectionist", "in", "a", "theater", "and", "mr", "tante", "be", "the", "projectionist", "in", "that", "theater"]]}, {"text": "The fine imposed on Mr. Tante and Ms. Allen was a $5,000 fine and 12 months on probation... that was after the conviction.", "start": 144.624, "stop": 157.784, "duration": 13.16, "cleanText": [["the", "fine", "impose", "on", "mr", "tante", "and", "ms", "allen", "be", "a", "fine", "and", "month", "on", "probation", "that", "be", "after", "the", "conviction"]]}, {"text": "They were to pay that fine as directed, which was $500 per month, so they would have paid the fine in approximately 10 months.", "start": 157.784, "stop": 166.39, "duration": 8.61, "cleanText": [["they", "we", "be", "to", "pay", "that", "fine", "as", "direct", "which", "be", "per", "month", "so", "they", "would", "have", "pay", "the", "fine", "in", "approximately", "month"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "And that was a condition of the probation was it not?", "start": 166.39, "stop": 167.89, "duration": 1.5, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "a", "condition", "of", "the", "probation", "be", "it", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 167.89, "stop": 169.759, "duration": 1.87, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Wood was convicted in two counts and he received a $5,000 fine in each count, to run consecutively, and 12 months on probation.", "start": 169.759, "stop": 183.183, "duration": 13.42, "cleanText": [["mr", "wood", "be", "convict", "in", "two", "count", "and", "he", "receive", "a", "fine", "in", "each", "count", "to", "run", "consecutively", "and", "month", "on", "probation"]]}, {"text": "Therefore, he had a 24-month sentence and a $10,000 fine, payable again at the rate of $500 per month over a period of 20 months.", "start": 183.183, "stop": 193.291, "duration": 10.11, "cleanText": [["therefore", "he", "have", "a", "month", "sentence", "and", "a", "fine", "payable", "again", "at", "the", "rate", "of", "per", "month", "over", "a", "period", "of", "month"]]}, {"text": "Thereafter I appealed the case to the Georgia Court of Appeals, and I lost.", "start": 193.291, "stop": 199.961, "duration": 6.67, "cleanText": [["thereafter", "i", "appeal", "the", "case", "to", "the", "georgia", "court", "of", "appeal", "and", "i", "lose"]]}, {"text": "I then certioraried the Georgia Supreme Court and certiorari was denied.", "start": 199.961, "stop": 204.599, "duration": 4.64, "cleanText": [["i", "then", "certioraried", "the", "georgia", "supreme", "court", "and", "certiorari", "be", "deny"]]}, {"text": "I then certioraried this Court, and cert was denied with some justices dissenting.", "start": 204.599, "stop": 210.151, "duration": 5.55, "cleanText": [["i", "then", "certioraried", "this", "court", "and", "cert", "be", "deny", "with", "some", "justice", "dissent"]]}, {"text": "The case came back to the trial court, through remittitur, that is, and of course while the case was on appeal in Georgia, as in most states in the federal system, the three Petitioners, or offenders, defendants, were not on probation.", "start": 210.151, "stop": 225.762, "duration": 15.61, "cleanText": [["the", "case", "come", "back", "to", "the", "trial", "court", "through", "remittitur", "that", "be", "and", "of", "course", "while", "the", "case", "be", "on", "appeal", "in", "georgia", "as", "in", "most", "state", "in", "the", "federal", "system", "the", "three", "petitioner", "or", "offender", "defendant", "we", "be", "not", "on", "probation"]]}, {"text": "The conviction, I think, was in March of '77, the remittiturs came back in October of 1978, and at that point, the three offenders, the three defendants, started serving their probation, right at the last week of October.", "start": 225.762, "stop": 242.222, "duration": 16.46, "cleanText": [["the", "conviction", "i", "think", "be", "in", "march", "of", "the", "remittiturs", "come", "back", "in", "october", "of", "and", "at", "that", "point", "the", "three", "offender", "the", "three", "defendant", "start", "serve", "their", "probation", "right", "at", "the", "last", "week", "of", "october"]]}, {"text": "And the record shows that the probation officers told each one... there was a different officer for each defendant... I don't know whether there were three different probation officers... but anyway, each one said you must pay your fine at the end of next month, at the rate of $500 per month.", "start": 242.222, "stop": 256.298, "duration": 14.08, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "record", "show", "that", "the", "probation", "officer", "tell", "each", "one", "there", "be", "a", "different", "officer", "for", "each", "defendant", "i", "do", "not", "know", "whether", "there", "we", "be", "three", "different", "probation", "officer", "but", "anyway", "each", "one", "say", "you", "must", "pay", "your", "fine", "at", "the", "end", "of", "next", "month", "at", "the", "rate", "of", "per", "month"]]}, {"text": "In the record, at page 71, I notified the Court immediately when they were put on probation that they did not have the funds and the fines should be remitted or suspended or some action taken, because there's going to be a problem in this case on this $20,000 in fines.", "start": 256.298, "stop": 274.693, "duration": 18.39, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "record", "at", "page", "i", "notify", "the", "court", "immediately", "when", "they", "we", "be", "put", "on", "probation", "that", "they", "do", "not", "have", "the", "fund", "and", "the", "fine", "should", "be", "remit", "or", "suspend", "or", "some", "action", "take", "because", "there", "be", "go", "to", "be", "a", "problem", "in", "this", "case", "on", "this", "in", "fine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "On your theory, then, the Court is powerless to impose any punishments?", "start": 274.693, "stop": 279.58, "duration": 4.89, "cleanText": [["on", "your", "theory", "then", "the", "court", "be", "powerless", "to", "impose", "any", "punishment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh no, the Court is certainly... has certain powers to enforce a... payments on the installment basis.", "start": 279.58, "stop": 287.853, "duration": 8.27, "cleanText": [["oh", "no", "the", "court", "be", "certainly", "have", "certain", "power", "to", "enforce", "a", "payment", "on", "the", "installment", "basis"]]}, {"text": "Obviously you have your civil penalties certainly, garnishment, levy on any property.", "start": 287.853, "stop": 292.738, "duration": 4.88, "cleanText": [["obviously", "you", "have", "your", "civil", "penalty", "certainly", "garnishment", "levy", "on", "any", "property"]]}, {"text": "For example, Mr. Tante was a prison guard at this time, while he was on probation.", "start": 292.738, "stop": 298.891, "duration": 6.15, "cleanText": [["for", "example", "mr", "tante", "be", "a", "prison", "guard", "at", "this", "time", "while", "he", "be", "on", "probation"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Wood had a job at a trucking company, I believe, he could have been garnished.", "start": 298.891, "stop": 304.712, "duration": 5.82, "cleanText": [["mr", "wood", "have", "a", "job", "at", "a", "trucking", "company", "i", "believe", "he", "could", "have", "be", "garnish"]]}, {"text": "And Ms. Allen, unfortunately, was on unemployment compensation and I don't think you can garnish that, I'm not sure if you can.", "start": 304.712, "stop": 310.099, "duration": 5.39, "cleanText": [["and", "ms", "allen", "unfortunately", "be", "on", "unemployment", "compensation", "and", "i", "do", "not", "think", "you", "can", "garnish", "that", "I", "be", "not", "sure", "if", "you", "can"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well doesn't Georgia have some exemptions to its garnishment statute, for necessary expenses of living?", "start": 310.099, "stop": 320.824, "duration": 10.73, "cleanText": [["well", "do", "not", "georgia", "have", "some", "exemption", "to", "its", "garnishment", "statute", "for", "necessary", "expense", "of", "living"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, there's a certain percentage after... I think it's, it used to be 50 percent, and it's a little lower, but there's a certain percentage you can only take out for garnishment.", "start": 320.824, "stop": 330.096, "duration": 9.27, "cleanText": [["yes", "there", "be", "a", "certain", "percentage", "after", "i", "think", "it", "be", "it", "use", "to", "be", "percent", "and", "it", "be", "a", "little", "low", "but", "there", "be", "a", "certain", "percentage", "you", "can", "only", "take", "out", "for", "garnishment"]]}, {"text": "And certainly some small sum of money could have been affected by garnishment at this point.", "start": 330.096, "stop": 334.348, "duration": 4.25, "cleanText": [["and", "certainly", "some", "small", "sum", "of", "money", "could", "have", "be", "affect", "by", "garnishment", "at", "this", "point"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well so your complaint is not that a fine was levied on someone who couldn't pay it?", "start": 334.348, "stop": 345.455, "duration": 11.11, "cleanText": [["well", "so", "your", "complaint", "be", "not", "that", "a", "fine", "be", "levy", "on", "someone", "who", "could", "not", "pay", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Not at all.", "start": 345.455, "stop": 347.041, "duration": 1.59, "cleanText": [["not", "at", "all"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "But that the fine was too high?", "start": 347.041, "stop": 349.759, "duration": 2.72, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "the", "fine", "be", "too", "high"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Correct.", "start": 349.759, "stop": 350.459, "duration": 0.7, "cleanText": [["correct"]]}, {"text": "Well that, and commensurate with, first of all, the administration of justice... what do you do with people who violate the law, and the judge, trial judge, makes a determination that these people can be released on the streets, in society, in public.", "start": 350.459, "stop": 366.869, "duration": 16.41, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "and", "commensurate", "with", "first", "of", "all", "the", "administration", "of", "justice", "what", "do", "you", "do", "with", "people", "who", "violate", "the", "law", "and", "the", "judge", "trial", "judge", "make", "a", "determination", "that", "these", "people", "can", "be", "release", "on", "the", "street", "in", "society", "in", "public"]]}, {"text": "They are not a danger, they shouldn't be incarcerated, they shouldn't be warehoused... so to speak.", "start": 366.869, "stop": 372.023, "duration": 5.15, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "not", "a", "danger", "they", "should", "not", "be", "incarcerate", "they", "should", "not", "be", "warehouse", "so", "to", "speak"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Zell, if you prevail here, what's going to happen: mandatory imprisonment in every case, of an indigent?", "start": 372.023, "stop": 381.528, "duration": 9.5, "cleanText": [["mr", "zell", "if", "you", "prevail", "here", "what", "be", "go", "to", "happen", "mandatory", "imprisonment", "in", "every", "case", "of", "an", "indigent"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I'd like to think, in our system of justice, that trial judges will not take that position.", "start": 381.528, "stop": 387.432, "duration": 5.9, "cleanText": [["well", "I", "would", "like", "to", "think", "in", "our", "system", "of", "justice", "that", "trial", "judge", "will", "not", "take", "that", "position"]]}, {"text": "I'm sure some will.", "start": 387.432, "stop": 389.218, "duration": 1.79, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sure", "some", "will"]]}, {"text": "And I'd like to think that a trial judge--", "start": 389.218, "stop": 390.57, "duration": 1.35, "cleanText": [["and", "I", "would", "like", "to", "think", "that", "a", "trial", "judge"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm asking whether your argument might turn out to be counter productive?", "start": 390.57, "stop": 394.938, "duration": 4.37, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "ask", "whether", "your", "argument", "might", "turn", "out", "to", "be", "counter", "productive"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It could, yes.", "start": 394.938, "stop": 396.338, "duration": 1.4, "cleanText": [["it", "could", "yes"]]}, {"text": "I'm aware of... some trial judges have told me that if they can't lock up an indigent defendant on probation, they're going to get straight time sentences.", "start": 396.338, "stop": 405.746, "duration": 9.41, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "aware", "of", "some", "trial", "judge", "have", "tell", "me", "that", "if", "they", "can", "not", "lock", "up", "an", "indigent", "defendant", "on", "probation", "they", "be", "go", "to", "get", "straight", "time", "sentence"]]}, {"text": "I'm sure that's a possibility.", "start": 405.746, "stop": 407.246, "duration": 1.5, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sure", "that", "be", "a", "possibility"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "My other question is, have these prison sentences been served?", "start": 407.246, "stop": 410.632, "duration": 3.39, "cleanText": [["my", "other", "question", "be", "have", "these", "prison", "sentence", "be", "serve"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "In this case?", "start": 410.632, "stop": 411.417, "duration": 0.78, "cleanText": [["in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 411.417, "stop": 411.967, "duration": 0.55, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh no, they've been... the judge let them stay out on bond pending this appeal, because they would have served their sentence if they had been incarcerated.", "start": 411.967, "stop": 419.804, "duration": 7.84, "cleanText": [["oh", "no", "they", "have", "be", "the", "judge", "let", "them", "stay", "out", "on", "bond", "pending", "this", "appeal", "because", "they", "would", "have", "serve", "their", "sentence", "if", "they", "have", "be", "incarcerate"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "So they... their sentences have been stayed?", "start": 419.804, "stop": 421.839, "duration": 2.04, "cleanText": [["so", "they", "their", "sentence", "have", "be", "stay"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 421.839, "stop": 422.639, "duration": 0.8, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "And they have not been served?", "start": 422.639, "stop": 423.775, "duration": 1.14, "cleanText": [["and", "they", "have", "not", "be", "serve"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 423.775, "stop": 424.741, "duration": 0.97, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "What were the sentences?", "start": 424.741, "stop": 426.491, "duration": 1.75, "cleanText": [["what", "we", "be", "the", "sentence"]]}, {"text": "Or, how much jail time will they spend?", "start": 426.491, "stop": 428.41, "duration": 1.92, "cleanText": [["or", "how", "much", "jail", "time", "will", "they", "spend"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Tante received... and Ms. Allen, received a 12-month sentence each.", "start": 428.41, "stop": 434.396, "duration": 5.99, "cleanText": [["mr", "tante", "receive", "and", "ms", "allen", "receive", "a", "month", "sentence", "each"]]}, {"text": "Under the computation, this is a high and aggravated misdemeanor; they would serve, they get four days--", "start": 434.396, "stop": 440.383, "duration": 5.99, "cleanText": [["under", "the", "computation", "this", "be", "a", "high", "and", "aggravated", "misdemeanor", "they", "would", "serve", "they", "get", "four", "day"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I... but the sentence was... they were put on probation first, weren't they?", "start": 440.383, "stop": 446.204, "duration": 5.82, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "but", "the", "sentence", "be", "they", "we", "be", "put", "on", "probation", "first", "be", "not", "they"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes.", "start": 446.204, "stop": 446.654, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "And they served almost three months of that sentence.", "start": 446.654, "stop": 449.989, "duration": 3.33, "cleanText": [["and", "they", "serve", "almost", "three", "month", "of", "that", "sentence"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "And then--", "start": 449.989, "stop": 450.773, "duration": 0.78, "cleanText": [["and", "then"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "They have nine left.", "start": 450.773, "stop": 451.539, "duration": 0.77, "cleanText": [["they", "have", "nine", "leave"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--And was... the probation was the same length as their sentences?", "start": 451.539, "stop": 455.143, "duration": 3.6, "cleanText": [["and", "be", "the", "probation", "be", "the", "same", "length", "as", "their", "sentence"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 455.143, "stop": 455.743, "duration": 0.6, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "I see.", "start": 455.743, "stop": 456.26, "duration": 0.52, "cleanText": [["i", "see"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 456.26, "stop": 456.727, "duration": 0.47, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "So they go back and serve their--", "start": 456.727, "stop": 458.512, "duration": 1.79, "cleanText": [["so", "they", "go", "back", "and", "serve", "their"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Nine months less good time, which is four days a month in this case; which would be 36 days less nine months, and they'd serve about eight months.", "start": 458.512, "stop": 465.916, "duration": 7.4, "cleanText": [["nine", "month", "less", "good", "time", "which", "be", "four", "day", "a", "month", "in", "this", "case", "which", "would", "be", "day", "less", "nine", "month", "and", "they", "would", "serve", "about", "eight", "month"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Wood has 2 years, 24 months on probation; he has served, again, three months, so he has 21 left to go, less four days a month, for the remaining 21 months--", "start": 465.916, "stop": 475.89, "duration": 9.97, "cleanText": [["mr", "wood", "have", "year", "month", "on", "probation", "he", "have", "serve", "again", "three", "month", "so", "he", "have", "left", "to", "go", "less", "four", "day", "a", "month", "for", "the", "remain", "month"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Does this record show from what resources their bond was provided, if they were indigent and couldn't pay the fine, the bond cost them some money, I suppose, in Georgia?", "start": 475.89, "stop": 484.929, "duration": 9.04, "cleanText": [["do", "this", "record", "show", "from", "what", "resource", "their", "bond", "be", "provide", "if", "they", "we", "be", "indigent", "and", "could", "not", "pay", "the", "fine", "the", "bond", "cost", "them", "some", "money", "i", "suppose", "in", "georgia"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes.", "start": 484.929, "stop": 485.379, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "The bond was provided for by their previous employer.", "start": 485.379, "stop": 489.464, "duration": 4.08, "cleanText": [["the", "bond", "be", "provide", "for", "by", "their", "previous", "employer"]]}, {"text": "He put up the bond for them.", "start": 489.464, "stop": 492.833, "duration": 3.37, "cleanText": [["he", "put", "up", "the", "bond", "for", "them"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "What does this record show about their previous employer's practice in paying fines?", "start": 492.833, "stop": 496.387, "duration": 3.55, "cleanText": [["what", "do", "this", "record", "show", "about", "their", "previous", "employer", "s", "practice", "in", "pay", "fine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well what happened was, and it's in the record, of course, that they were first fined in this case, and then thereafter they were charged again in another case, so that each one was, and a small fine was imposed and paid by their employer.", "start": 496.387, "stop": 515.681, "duration": 19.29, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "happen", "be", "and", "it", "be", "in", "the", "record", "of", "course", "that", "they", "we", "be", "first", "fin", "in", "this", "case", "and", "then", "thereafter", "they", "we", "be", "charge", "again", "in", "another", "case", "so", "that", "each", "one", "be", "and", "a", "small", "fine", "be", "impose", "and", "pay", "by", "their", "employer"]]}, {"text": "Paid by their employer, through me... the fine was paid, and they received something like very small suspended sentences.", "start": 515.681, "stop": 522.019, "duration": 6.34, "cleanText": [["pay", "by", "their", "employer", "through", "me", "the", "fine", "be", "pay", "and", "they", "receive", "something", "like", "very", "small", "suspended", "sentence"]]}, {"text": "The fines, I might add, it's on the record, were much smaller than this case, they were $750 fines, something like that.", "start": 522.019, "stop": 528.173, "duration": 6.15, "cleanText": [["the", "fine", "i", "might", "add", "it", "be", "on", "the", "record", "we", "be", "much", "small", "than", "this", "case", "they", "we", "be", "fine", "something", "like", "that"]]}, {"text": "And then when the remittitur came down in the first appeal, they were... the employer did not pay the fines in this case, for certain reasons such as a different change of attitude and a different employer--", "start": 528.173, "stop": 539.214, "duration": 11.04, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "when", "the", "remittitur", "come", "down", "in", "the", "first", "appeal", "they", "we", "be", "the", "employer", "do", "not", "pay", "the", "fine", "in", "this", "case", "for", "certain", "reason", "such", "as", "a", "different", "change", "of", "attitude", "and", "a", "different", "employer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Are these Petitioners here in forma pauperis?", "start": 539.214, "stop": 541.916, "duration": 2.7, "cleanText": [["be", "these", "petitioner", "here", "in", "forma", "pauperis"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, that's correct.", "start": 541.916, "stop": 543.366, "duration": 1.45, "cleanText": [["yes", "that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well doesn't that suggest some validity to Mr. Justice Blackmun's observation, that if the people are before the Court, but not for the first time or the second time, but for the fifth time, and the Court feels that, you know, we don't want to warehouse these people and lock them up with murderers, but if we can't do anything else to them... if they are indigent, and small... or the small time fines haven't deterred them before, isn't there going to be a tendency to at least send them to the... some facility for confinement?", "start": 543.366, "stop": 585.462, "duration": 42.1, "cleanText": [["well", "do", "not", "that", "suggest", "some", "validity", "to", "mr", "justice", "blackmun", "s", "observation", "that", "if", "the", "people", "be", "before", "the", "court", "but", "not", "for", "the", "first", "time", "or", "the", "second", "time", "but", "for", "the", "fifth", "time", "and", "the", "court", "feel", "that", "you", "know", "we", "do", "not", "want", "to", "warehouse", "these", "people", "and", "lock", "them", "up", "with", "murderer", "but", "if", "we", "can", "not", "do", "anything", "else", "to", "them", "if", "they", "be", "indigent", "and", "small", "or", "the", "small", "time", "fine", "have", "not", "deter", "them", "before", "be", "not", "there", "go", "to", "be", "a", "tendency", "to", "at", "least", "send", "them", "to", "the", "some", "facility", "for", "confinement"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay, let me just relay a little chronology.", "start": 585.462, "stop": 588.414, "duration": 2.95, "cleanText": [["okay", "let", "me", "just", "relay", "a", "little", "chronology"]]}, {"text": "The second cases were imposed after this sentence.", "start": 588.414, "stop": 592.349, "duration": 3.94, "cleanText": [["the", "second", "case", "we", "be", "impose", "after", "this", "sentence"]]}, {"text": "Now this was their first conviction.", "start": 592.349, "stop": 594.484, "duration": 2.13, "cleanText": [["now", "this", "be", "their", "first", "conviction"]]}, {"text": "They stayed in the... stayed working at the theater and bookstore, and they were arrested and pled guilty and received a fine thereafter this sentence though.", "start": 594.484, "stop": 603.923, "duration": 9.44, "cleanText": [["they", "stay", "in", "the", "stay", "work", "at", "the", "theater", "and", "bookstore", "and", "they", "we", "be", "arrest", "and", "plead", "guilty", "and", "receive", "a", "fine", "thereafter", "this", "sentence", "though"]]}, {"text": "And thereafter, they were before different judges, and they received a much more modest fine, I think something under... less than a thousand dollars.", "start": 603.923, "stop": 612.279, "duration": 8.36, "cleanText": [["and", "thereafter", "they", "we", "be", "before", "different", "judge", "and", "they", "receive", "a", "much", "more", "modest", "fine", "i", "think", "something", "under", "less", "than", "a", "thousand", "dollar"]]}, {"text": "And it was paid by their employer because they were working there, they were useful to the employer to keep working at the theater and bookstore.", "start": 612.279, "stop": 618.749, "duration": 6.47, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "be", "pay", "by", "their", "employer", "because", "they", "we", "be", "work", "there", "they", "we", "be", "useful", "to", "the", "employer", "to", "keep", "work", "at", "the", "theater", "and", "bookstore"]]}, {"text": "Then when they went on probation they had to quit.", "start": 618.749, "stop": 622.301, "duration": 3.55, "cleanText": [["then", "when", "they", "go", "on", "probation", "they", "have", "to", "quit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well is that really a very commendable motive, that the employer pays their fine because they were convicted of doing something that was illegal under Georgia law?", "start": 622.301, "stop": 633.443, "duration": 11.14, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "that", "really", "a", "very", "commendable", "motive", "that", "the", "employer", "pay", "their", "fine", "because", "they", "we", "be", "convict", "of", "do", "something", "that", "be", "illegal", "under", "georgia", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well certainly you can't enforce any agreement between the employer and the employee, it would be against public policy, like enforcing a gambling contract; he promised to pay it, in some instances he did pay the fine.", "start": 633.443, "stop": 643.731, "duration": 10.29, "cleanText": [["well", "certainly", "you", "can", "not", "enforce", "any", "agreement", "between", "the", "employer", "and", "the", "employee", "it", "would", "be", "against", "public", "policy", "like", "enforce", "a", "gambling", "contract", "he", "promise", "to", "pay", "it", "in", "some", "instance", "he", "do", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}, {"text": "As soon as they left work, he didn't pay the fines.", "start": 643.731, "stop": 648.035, "duration": 4.3, "cleanText": [["as", "soon", "as", "they", "leave", "work", "he", "do", "not", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is this a common provision in Georgia, between employees of so called adult bookstores and their employers?", "start": 648.035, "stop": 659.01, "duration": 10.98, "cleanText": [["be", "this", "a", "common", "provision", "in", "georgia", "between", "employee", "of", "so", "call", "adult", "bookstore", "and", "their", "employer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes and no.", "start": 659.01, "stop": 660.743, "duration": 1.73, "cleanText": [["yes", "and", "no"]]}, {"text": "It... many times the employer has paid the fines for employees, many times... many times he has not.", "start": 660.743, "stop": 665.728, "duration": 4.98, "cleanText": [["it", "many", "time", "the", "employer", "have", "pay", "the", "fine", "for", "employee", "many", "time", "many", "time", "he", "have", "not"]]}, {"text": "I just filed a cert in this court last week involving a case called Simpson v. Georgia, in which he received a $20,000 fine in a different theater, different business, and he's supposed to pay $1,000 a month.", "start": 665.728, "stop": 679.621, "duration": 13.89, "cleanText": [["i", "just", "file", "a", "cert", "in", "this", "court", "last", "week", "involve", "a", "case", "call", "simpson", "v", "georgia", "in", "which", "he", "receive", "a", "fine", "in", "a", "different", "theater", "different", "business", "and", "he", "be", "suppose", "to", "pay", "a", "month"]]}, {"text": "And he was a short order cook.", "start": 679.621, "stop": 682.156, "duration": 2.53, "cleanText": [["and", "he", "be", "a", "short", "order", "cook"]]}, {"text": "And the judge again revoked his probation because he did not pay the $1,000 a month.", "start": 682.156, "stop": 687.893, "duration": 5.74, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "judge", "again", "revoke", "his", "probation", "because", "he", "do", "not", "pay", "the", "a", "month"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Zell, do you have pre sentence reports in Georgia?", "start": 687.893, "stop": 691.095, "duration": 3.2, "cleanText": [["mr", "zell", "do", "you", "have", "pre", "sentence", "report", "in", "georgia"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 691.095, "stop": 691.895, "duration": 0.8, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well don't they show how much a man is worth?", "start": 691.895, "stop": 693.547, "duration": 1.65, "cleanText": [["well", "do", "not", "they", "show", "how", "much", "a", "man", "be", "worth"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 693.547, "stop": 695.43, "duration": 1.88, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "So the judge knew that he had enough money to pay that fine, didn't he?", "start": 695.43, "stop": 699.284, "duration": 3.85, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "judge", "know", "that", "he", "have", "enough", "money", "to", "pay", "that", "fine", "do", "not", "he"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well what happened--", "start": 699.284, "stop": 700.218, "duration": 0.93, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "happen"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Can I assume that?", "start": 700.218, "stop": 702.07, "duration": 1.85, "cleanText": [["can", "i", "assume", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The judge knew... well here's what happened, Your Honor... being, as a practical matter, when they were convicted in the first instance, the judge, Judge Alexander, was aware of what they were doing; they were making nominal amounts of money as a clerk/projectionist.", "start": 702.07, "stop": 716.311, "duration": 14.24, "cleanText": [["the", "judge", "know", "well", "here", "s", "what", "happen", "your", "honor", "be", "as", "a", "practical", "matter", "when", "they", "we", "be", "convict", "in", "the", "first", "instance", "the", "judge", "judge", "alexander", "be", "aware", "of", "what", "they", "we", "be", "do", "they", "we", "be", "make", "nominal", "amount", "of", "money", "as", "a", "clerkprojectionist"]]}, {"text": "I'm sure the judge thought, it's rather obvious from the record, that he thought if he imposed this large fine their employer would pay it.", "start": 716.311, "stop": 724.566, "duration": 8.25, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sure", "the", "judge", "thought", "it", "be", "rather", "obvious", "from", "the", "record", "that", "he", "think", "if", "he", "impose", "this", "large", "fine", "their", "employer", "would", "pay", "it"]]}, {"text": "I'm sure that was the thrust of why the fine was so heavy, was so large, your employer will pay it, based on maybe other... other cases, or at prodding of the prosecutors, saying fine and dandy, don't worry, it will be taken care of.", "start": 724.566, "stop": 737.909, "duration": 13.34, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sure", "that", "be", "the", "thrust", "of", "why", "the", "fine", "be", "so", "heavy", "be", "so", "large", "your", "employer", "will", "pay", "it", "base", "on", "maybe", "other", "other", "case", "or", "at", "prodding", "of", "the", "prosecutor", "say", "fine", "and", "dandy", "do", "not", "worry", "it", "will", "be", "take", "care", "of"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "But the employer was just treating this as a cost of doing business, sort of a--", "start": 737.909, "stop": 740.861, "duration": 2.95, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "employer", "be", "just", "treat", "this", "as", "a", "cost", "of", "do", "business", "sort", "of", "a"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 740.861, "stop": 741.311, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "--licensing fee?", "start": 741.311, "stop": 742.295, "duration": 0.98, "cleanText": [["license", "fee"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct, sort of licensing, that's correct.", "start": 742.295, "stop": 744.48, "duration": 2.19, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "sort", "of", "licensing", "that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "But he is here in forma pauperis, now?", "start": 744.48, "stop": 748.365, "duration": 3.88, "cleanText": [["but", "he", "be", "here", "in", "forma", "pauperis", "now"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 748.365, "stop": 749.249, "duration": 0.88, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "These people are the mere employees--", "start": 749.249, "stop": 752.017, "duration": 2.77, "cleanText": [["these", "people", "be", "the", "mere", "employee"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, the employees.", "start": 752.017, "stop": 753.017, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["oh", "the", "employee"]]}, {"text": "What would happen if--", "start": 753.017, "stop": 755.385, "duration": 2.37, "cleanText": [["what", "would", "happen", "if"]]}, {"text": "--But they're not working there anymore?", "start": 755.385, "stop": 756.585, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["but", "they", "be", "not", "work", "there", "anymore"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That's right.", "start": 756.585, "stop": 757.202, "duration": 0.62, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "What would happen if the pre sentence report shows that Mr. Jones has a friend by the name of Mr. Smith and Mr. Smith will give him a thousand dollars, and they fined him a thousand dollars, and they're not working together or anything, this is just a friend; would the Court be entitled to go back on that?", "start": 757.202, "stop": 783.636, "duration": 26.43, "cleanText": [["what", "would", "happen", "if", "the", "pre", "sentence", "report", "show", "that", "mr", "jones", "have", "a", "friend", "by", "the", "name", "of", "mr", "smith", "and", "mr", "smith", "will", "give", "him", "a", "thousand", "dollar", "and", "they", "fin", "him", "a", "thousand", "dollar", "and", "they", "be", "not", "work", "together", "or", "anything", "this", "be", "just", "a", "friend", "would", "the", "court", "be", "entitle", "to", "go", "back", "on", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well,--", "start": 783.636, "stop": 784.102, "duration": 0.47, "cleanText": [["well"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "On the fact that he used some bad information?", "start": 784.102, "stop": 789.123, "duration": 5.02, "cleanText": [["on", "the", "fact", "that", "he", "use", "some", "bad", "information"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Certainly, he should, the Court... again--", "start": 789.123, "stop": 791.392, "duration": 2.27, "cleanText": [["certainly", "he", "should", "the", "court", "again"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well when you get through, I want to know the difference between that case and this case.", "start": 791.392, "stop": 794.11, "duration": 2.72, "cleanText": [["well", "when", "you", "get", "through", "i", "want", "to", "know", "the", "difference", "between", "that", "case", "and", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well certainly he should... the judge should modify the condition of probation and the fine... if there was some misinformation.", "start": 794.11, "stop": 799.831, "duration": 5.72, "cleanText": [["well", "certainly", "he", "should", "the", "judge", "should", "modify", "the", "condition", "of", "probation", "and", "the", "fine", "if", "there", "be", "some", "misinformation"]]}, {"text": "Obviously, or even a promise by the defendant... how many defendants can afford--", "start": 799.831, "stop": 803.783, "duration": 3.95, "cleanText": [["obviously", "or", "even", "a", "promise", "by", "the", "defendant", "how", "many", "defendant", "can", "afford"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would you at that time tell the judge that the man couldn't pay the fine?", "start": 803.783, "stop": 811.222, "duration": 7.44, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "at", "that", "time", "tell", "the", "judge", "that", "the", "man", "could", "not", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, there was no representation made.", "start": 811.222, "stop": 813.356, "duration": 2.13, "cleanText": [["no", "there", "be", "no", "representation", "make"]]}, {"text": "The trial was--", "start": 813.356, "stop": 814.173, "duration": 0.82, "cleanText": [["the", "trial", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "You'd just let the judge go down that road?", "start": 814.173, "stop": 816.959, "duration": 2.79, "cleanText": [["you", "would", "just", "let", "the", "judge", "go", "down", "that", "road"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That's correct.", "start": 816.959, "stop": 817.325, "duration": 0.37, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "What happened is,--", "start": 817.325, "stop": 818.909, "duration": 1.58, "cleanText": [["what", "happen", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Now you want to complain about the judge?", "start": 818.909, "stop": 822.294, "duration": 3.38, "cleanText": [["now", "you", "want", "to", "complain", "about", "the", "judge"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, I mean that's--", "start": 822.294, "stop": 823.279, "duration": 0.99, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "mean", "that", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "You're not complaining about yourself at all, are you?", "start": 823.279, "stop": 825.346, "duration": 2.07, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "not", "complain", "about", "yourself", "at", "all", "be", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, what happened is, the trial was over.", "start": 825.346, "stop": 828.181, "duration": 2.84, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "happen", "be", "the", "trial", "be", "over"]]}, {"text": "The jury returned a verdict of guilty.", "start": 828.181, "stop": 831.183, "duration": 3, "cleanText": [["the", "jury", "return", "a", "verdict", "of", "guilty"]]}, {"text": "At that point, the prosecutor... and it's not in the record, but I can... prodded the judge to impose a large fine.", "start": 831.183, "stop": 838.456, "duration": 7.27, "cleanText": [["at", "that", "point", "the", "prosecutor", "and", "it", "be", "not", "in", "the", "record", "but", "i", "can", "prod", "the", "judge", "to", "impose", "a", "large", "fine"]]}, {"text": "That normally is done in these cases, large fines.", "start": 838.456, "stop": 842.341, "duration": 3.88, "cleanText": [["that", "normally", "be", "do", "in", "these", "case", "large", "fine"]]}, {"text": "The judge was aware of their employment and I think the judge, as in many of these cases, felt that a third party would pay the fine.", "start": 842.341, "stop": 852.799, "duration": 10.46, "cleanText": [["the", "judge", "be", "aware", "of", "their", "employment", "and", "i", "think", "the", "judge", "as", "in", "many", "of", "these", "case", "felt", "that", "a", "third", "party", "would", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}, {"text": "There was no... we do not tell the judge the third party would pay the fine; we just... the judge was aware of the facts.", "start": 852.799, "stop": 859.119, "duration": 6.32, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "we", "do", "not", "tell", "the", "judge", "the", "third", "party", "would", "pay", "the", "fine", "we", "just", "the", "judge", "be", "aware", "of", "the", "fact"]]}, {"text": "I did not know if the third party would pay the fine at that point, there was no guarantee, so to speak, at that point.", "start": 859.119, "stop": 864.44, "duration": 5.32, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know", "if", "the", "third", "party", "would", "pay", "the", "fine", "at", "that", "point", "there", "be", "no", "guarantee", "so", "to", "speak", "at", "that", "point"]]}, {"text": "The case was then appealed.", "start": 864.44, "stop": 866.406, "duration": 1.97, "cleanText": [["the", "case", "be", "then", "appeal"]]}, {"text": "We did not... they asked for a large fine, it was just a prodding of the prosecutor, and--", "start": 866.406, "stop": 872.826, "duration": 6.42, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "not", "they", "ask", "for", "a", "large", "fine", "it", "be", "just", "a", "prodding", "of", "the", "prosecutor", "and"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you didn't represent the third party, you represented this man?", "start": 872.826, "stop": 875.778, "duration": 2.95, "cleanText": [["but", "you", "do", "not", "represent", "the", "third", "party", "you", "represent", "this", "man"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--At... during the trial in the first instance, that's correct.", "start": 875.778, "stop": 877.728, "duration": 1.95, "cleanText": [["at", "during", "the", "trial", "in", "the", "first", "instance", "that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "You still do?", "start": 877.728, "stop": 878.88, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["you", "still", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Represent the third party?", "start": 878.88, "stop": 880.314, "duration": 1.43, "cleanText": [["represent", "the", "third", "party"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 880.314, "stop": 881.166, "duration": 0.85, "cleanText": [["no"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "The defendants?", "start": 881.166, "stop": 882.316, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["the", "defendant"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 882.316, "stop": 882.849, "duration": 0.53, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 882.849, "stop": 883.666, "duration": 0.82, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "Oh, before this Court, yes, I do.", "start": 883.666, "stop": 884.701, "duration": 1.03, "cleanText": [["oh", "before", "this", "court", "yes", "i", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "You were not a court appointed counsel?", "start": 884.701, "stop": 886.468, "duration": 1.77, "cleanText": [["you", "we", "be", "not", "a", "court", "appoint", "counsel"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct, I was not.", "start": 886.468, "stop": 888.585, "duration": 2.12, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "i", "be", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "So he's here as an indigent, in forma pauperis, but he has paid counsel, then, I take it?", "start": 888.585, "stop": 895.556, "duration": 6.97, "cleanText": [["so", "he", "have", "here", "as", "an", "indigent", "in", "forma", "pauperis", "but", "he", "have", "pay", "counsel", "then", "i", "take", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 895.556, "stop": 896.108, "duration": 0.55, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "The defendants in this case, the way it came about, was, I received a call... I wrote the Court letter, felt obligated to let the Court know that the defendants did not have the money after the appeal was terminated, and they were no longer working for the owner of the theater, and I notified the Court that they did not have the funds and to please take some action, that they no longer worked in there and there was going to be some problem, they did not have the money and it would not be forthcoming.", "start": 896.108, "stop": 919.624, "duration": 23.52, "cleanText": [["the", "defendant", "in", "this", "case", "the", "way", "it", "come", "about", "be", "i", "receive", "a", "call", "i", "write", "the", "court", "letter", "felt", "obligate", "to", "let", "the", "court", "know", "that", "the", "defendant", "do", "not", "have", "the", "money", "after", "the", "appeal", "be", "terminate", "and", "they", "we", "be", "no", "longer", "work", "for", "the", "owner", "of", "the", "theater", "and", "i", "notify", "the", "court", "that", "they", "do", "not", "have", "the", "fund", "and", "to", "please", "take", "some", "action", "that", "they", "no", "longer", "work", "in", "there", "and", "there", "be", "go", "to", "be", "some", "problem", "they", "do", "not", "have", "the", "money", "and", "it", "would", "not", "be", "forthcoming"]]}, {"text": "The Court chose not to take any action, this is in the record, page 71.", "start": 919.624, "stop": 924.309, "duration": 4.68, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "choose", "not", "to", "take", "any", "action", "this", "be", "in", "the", "record", "page"]]}, {"text": "And they continued to report on probation, and that's the last I heard of it.", "start": 924.309, "stop": 929.111, "duration": 4.8, "cleanText": [["and", "they", "continue", "to", "report", "on", "probation", "and", "that", "be", "the", "last", "i", "heard", "of", "it"]]}, {"text": "I then received a call, the first week of January, saying that they want you down in Court, that I represent these three defendants and would I come down to court to represent them.", "start": 929.111, "stop": 938.216, "duration": 9.11, "cleanText": [["i", "then", "receive", "a", "call", "the", "first", "week", "of", "january", "say", "that", "they", "want", "you", "down", "in", "court", "that", "i", "represent", "these", "three", "defendant", "and", "would", "i", "come", "down", "to", "court", "to", "represent", "them"]]}, {"text": "I contacted the three defendants and I asked them, did they have money for counsel and did they want me to represent them, I would be glad to.", "start": 938.216, "stop": 944.286, "duration": 6.07, "cleanText": [["i", "contact", "the", "three", "defendant", "and", "i", "ask", "them", "do", "they", "have", "money", "for", "counsel", "and", "do", "they", "want", "me", "to", "represent", "them", "i", "would", "be", "glad", "to"]]}, {"text": "And they said yes, we want you as our lawyer, you're familiar with our case.", "start": 944.286, "stop": 947.322, "duration": 3.04, "cleanText": [["and", "they", "say", "yes", "we", "want", "you", "as", "our", "lawyer", "you", "be", "familiar", "with", "our", "case"]]}, {"text": "And so I went down to court to represent them at that point.", "start": 947.322, "stop": 950.874, "duration": 3.55, "cleanText": [["and", "so", "i", "go", "down", "to", "court", "to", "represent", "them", "at", "that", "point"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "You received a call from the Court.", "start": 950.874, "stop": 953.742, "duration": 2.87, "cleanText": [["you", "receive", "a", "call", "from", "the", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Several... from the defendants, from the Court, from the solicitor... concerning the hearing, I received a notice of the hearing date, and of course, the defendants called me and notified me that they were in some trouble and what could I do for them.", "start": 953.742, "stop": 965.784, "duration": 12.04, "cleanText": [["several", "from", "the", "defendant", "from", "the", "court", "from", "the", "solicitor", "concern", "the", "hearing", "i", "receive", "a", "notice", "of", "the", "hearing", "date", "and", "of", "course", "the", "defendant", "call", "me", "and", "notify", "me", "that", "they", "we", "be", "in", "some", "trouble", "and", "what", "could", "i", "do", "for", "them"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "But not from the third party?", "start": 965.784, "stop": 967.819, "duration": 2.03, "cleanText": [["but", "not", "from", "the", "third", "party"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, that's correct; not from a third party.", "start": 967.819, "stop": 969.419, "duration": 1.6, "cleanText": [["no", "that", "be", "correct", "not", "from", "a", "third", "party"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "I still want to know, you represent them officially here?", "start": 969.419, "stop": 972.203, "duration": 2.78, "cleanText": [["i", "still", "want", "to", "know", "you", "represent", "them", "officially", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "The defendants.", "start": 972.203, "stop": 973.153, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["the", "defendant"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "And not the third party?", "start": 973.153, "stop": 976.189, "duration": 3.04, "cleanText": [["and", "not", "the", "third", "party"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 976.189, "stop": 976.774, "duration": 0.59, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "I have not been paid for this case and that's in the record.", "start": 976.774, "stop": 980.059, "duration": 3.28, "cleanText": [["i", "have", "not", "be", "pay", "for", "this", "case", "and", "that", "be", "in", "the", "record"]]}, {"text": "I think the solicitor brought that out aptly during the trial that I had represented the defendants, but I was paid by the theater owner at the time of the trial, when they were working for the theater owner.", "start": 980.059, "stop": 992.283, "duration": 12.22, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "the", "solicitor", "bring", "that", "out", "aptly", "during", "the", "trial", "that", "i", "have", "represent", "the", "defendant", "but", "i", "be", "pay", "by", "the", "theater", "owner", "at", "the", "time", "of", "the", "trial", "when", "they", "we", "be", "work", "for", "the", "theater", "owner"]]}, {"text": "But as soon as they were put on probation their employment was terminated and therefore the ties were severed with the third party, or the employer.", "start": 992.283, "stop": 1000.121, "duration": 7.84, "cleanText": [["but", "as", "soon", "as", "they", "we", "be", "put", "on", "probation", "their", "employment", "be", "terminate", "and", "therefore", "the", "tie", "we", "be", "sever", "with", "the", "third", "party", "or", "the", "employer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's clear, isn't it, Mr. Zell, that the monthly installment repayments were conditions of the probation?", "start": 1000.121, "stop": 1008.242, "duration": 8.12, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "clear", "be", "not", "it", "mr", "zell", "that", "the", "monthly", "installment", "repayment", "we", "be", "condition", "of", "the", "probation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Absolutely.", "start": 1008.242, "stop": 1008.959, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["absolutely"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "It was made clear that were these repayments not made the probation would be revoked and the custodial sentences would be imposed?", "start": 1008.959, "stop": 1017.248, "duration": 8.29, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "make", "clear", "that", "we", "be", "these", "repayment", "not", "make", "the", "probation", "would", "be", "revoke", "and", "the", "custodial", "sentence", "would", "be", "impose"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay.", "start": 1017.248, "stop": 1018.014, "duration": 0.77, "cleanText": [["okay"]]}, {"text": "At that point, the fines were imposed, that's correct.", "start": 1018.014, "stop": 1021.283, "duration": 3.27, "cleanText": [["at", "that", "point", "the", "fine", "we", "be", "impose", "that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "There was no--", "start": 1021.283, "stop": 1021.966, "duration": 0.68, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "It was made clear that it was a condition of the probation?", "start": 1021.966, "stop": 1024.235, "duration": 2.27, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "make", "clear", "that", "it", "be", "a", "condition", "of", "the", "probation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Absolutely, yes.", "start": 1024.235, "stop": 1024.868, "duration": 0.63, "cleanText": [["absolutely", "yes"]]}, {"text": "It was a condition of probation.", "start": 1024.868, "stop": 1025.935, "duration": 1.07, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "a", "condition", "of", "probation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, would it be... and it's not contended that the prison sentences imposed, which were probated in this case temporarily, were excessive, under the law... they were authorized by statute?", "start": 1025.935, "stop": 1046.248, "duration": 20.31, "cleanText": [["well", "would", "it", "be", "and", "it", "be", "not", "contend", "that", "the", "prison", "sentence", "impose", "which", "we", "be", "probate", "in", "this", "case", "temporarily", "we", "be", "excessive", "under", "the", "law", "they", "we", "be", "authorize", "by", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Within the statute, yes.", "start": 1046.248, "stop": 1047.433, "duration": 1.18, "cleanText": [["within", "the", "statute", "yes"]]}, {"text": "They were... that is, the maximum fine is $5,000.", "start": 1047.433, "stop": 1049.819, "duration": 2.39, "cleanText": [["they", "we", "be", "that", "be", "the", "maximum", "fine", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would it be permissible for a judge to impose an authorized prison sentence and probate it, depending say, on the condition that the defendant, convicted defendant stand on his head at twelve noon every day?", "start": 1049.819, "stop": 1073.083, "duration": 23.26, "cleanText": [["would", "it", "be", "permissible", "for", "a", "judge", "to", "impose", "an", "authorized", "prison", "sentence", "and", "probate", "it", "depend", "say", "on", "the", "condition", "that", "the", "defendant", "convict", "defendant", "stand", "on", "his", "head", "at", "twelve", "noon", "every", "day"]]}, {"text": "And then if it turned out that the defendant couldn't... didn't know how to stand on his head he would go to prison?", "start": 1073.083, "stop": 1078.885, "duration": 5.8, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "if", "it", "turn", "out", "that", "the", "defendant", "could", "not", "do", "not", "know", "how", "to", "stand", "on", "his", "head", "he", "would", "go", "to", "prison"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think that's the reach in this case.", "start": 1078.885, "stop": 1080.387, "duration": 1.5, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "be", "the", "reach", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "It's just an unreasonable condition.", "start": 1080.387, "stop": 1082.104, "duration": 1.72, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "just", "an", "unreasonable", "condition"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well what, and let's say the judge knew at the time he imposed the probated sentence, that the defendant, the convict didn't know how to stand on his head?", "start": 1082.104, "stop": 1090.96, "duration": 8.86, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "and", "let", "us", "say", "the", "judge", "know", "at", "the", "time", "he", "impose", "the", "probated", "sentence", "that", "the", "defendant", "the", "convict", "do", "not", "know", "how", "to", "stand", "on", "his", "head"]]}, {"text": "If he could have imposed the prison sentence from the word go, couldn't he have imposed a... an impossible condition?", "start": 1090.96, "stop": 1101.833, "duration": 10.87, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "could", "have", "impose", "the", "prison", "sentence", "from", "the", "word", "go", "could", "not", "he", "have", "impose", "a", "an", "impossible", "condition"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "It becomes... that's correct, it was an illusory sentence, gives them a taste of liberty to see what they could raise, and if you can't raise the money, in prison you go.", "start": 1101.833, "stop": 1109.856, "duration": 8.02, "cleanText": [["it", "become", "that", "be", "correct", "it", "be", "an", "illusory", "sentence", "give", "them", "a", "taste", "of", "liberty", "to", "see", "what", "they", "could", "raise", "and", "if", "you", "can", "not", "raise", "the", "money", "in", "prison", "you", "go"]]}, {"text": "It's really an illusory sentence.", "start": 1109.856, "stop": 1112.224, "duration": 2.37, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "really", "an", "illusory", "sentence"]]}, {"text": "That's what I point out in my brief.", "start": 1112.224, "stop": 1113.208, "duration": 0.98, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "what", "i", "point", "out", "in", "my", "brief"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, from the point of view of the Defendants, isn't it better than a straight sentence from the beginning?", "start": 1113.208, "stop": 1118.878, "duration": 5.67, "cleanText": [["well", "from", "the", "point", "of", "view", "of", "the", "defendant", "be", "not", "it", "good", "than", "a", "straight", "sentence", "from", "the", "beginning"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "No question about it.", "start": 1118.878, "stop": 1120.045, "duration": 1.17, "cleanText": [["no", "question", "about", "it"]]}, {"text": "But what do you do when the judge makes a determination and assume he did, that these people should not be put in prison?", "start": 1120.045, "stop": 1125.781, "duration": 5.74, "cleanText": [["but", "what", "do", "you", "do", "when", "the", "judge", "make", "a", "determination", "and", "assume", "he", "do", "that", "these", "people", "should", "not", "be", "put", "in", "prison"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well but wasn't part of his determination the fact that they would be subject to some penalty, i.e., the payment of a fine?", "start": 1125.781, "stop": 1135.156, "duration": 9.38, "cleanText": [["well", "but", "be", "not", "part", "of", "his", "determination", "the", "fact", "that", "they", "would", "be", "subject", "to", "some", "penalty", "ie", "the", "payment", "of", "a", "fine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well--", "start": 1135.156, "stop": 1136.206, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["well"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "He didn't intend to let them off scot free?", "start": 1136.206, "stop": 1138.275, "duration": 2.07, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "not", "intend", "to", "let", "them", "off", "scot", "free"]]}, {"text": "And it wasn't his decision, as indicated here, that they shouldn't be imprisoned if they paid $500 a month?", "start": 1138.275, "stop": 1143.76, "duration": 5.48, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "be", "not", "his", "decision", "as", "indicate", "here", "that", "they", "should", "not", "be", "imprison", "if", "they", "pay", "a", "month"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That's correct, that's correct.", "start": 1143.76, "stop": 1145.095, "duration": 1.34, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "Hoping that--", "start": 1145.095, "stop": 1145.829, "duration": 0.73, "cleanText": [["hop", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Otherwise that they should be, that's the implicit condition.", "start": 1145.829, "stop": 1148.547, "duration": 2.72, "cleanText": [["otherwise", "that", "they", "should", "be", "that", "be", "the", "implicit", "condition"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No question about it, that's correct.", "start": 1148.547, "stop": 1149.631, "duration": 1.08, "cleanText": [["no", "question", "about", "it", "that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "And all I'm saying before this Court is that when you have the situation, is that other alternatives should be made available to the Court, and for the Defendants, such as community service work, it would be much more constructive.", "start": 1149.631, "stop": 1163.24, "duration": 13.61, "cleanText": [["and", "all", "I", "be", "say", "before", "this", "court", "be", "that", "when", "you", "have", "the", "situation", "be", "that", "other", "alternative", "should", "be", "make", "available", "to", "the", "court", "and", "for", "the", "defendant", "such", "as", "community", "service", "work", "it", "would", "be", "much", "more", "constructive"]]}, {"text": "How does it serve the administration of justice, the prison system; for example, in Georgia,--", "start": 1163.24, "stop": 1168.21, "duration": 4.97, "cleanText": [["how", "do", "it", "serve", "the", "administration", "of", "justice", "the", "prison", "system", "for", "example", "in", "georgia"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well we're not running the Georgia prison system.", "start": 1168.21, "stop": 1171.496, "duration": 3.29, "cleanText": [["well", "we", "be", "not", "run", "the", "georgia", "prison", "system"]]}, {"text": "I mean, that's up to Georgia, to provide it, if it can... if it falls within the United States Constitution.", "start": 1171.496, "stop": 1179.352, "duration": 7.86, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "that", "be", "up", "to", "georgia", "to", "provide", "it", "if", "it", "can", "if", "it", "fall", "within", "the", "united", "state", "constitution"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, but how does that help further the objective in this case?", "start": 1179.352, "stop": 1184.72, "duration": 5.37, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "how", "do", "that", "help", "further", "the", "objective", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "Why do you want to incarcerate somebody for not having the money?", "start": 1184.72, "stop": 1187.439, "duration": 2.72, "cleanText": [["why", "do", "you", "want", "to", "incarcerate", "somebody", "for", "not", "have", "the", "money"]]}, {"text": "What... then you have this classification, suspect classification, poverty v. non poverty--", "start": 1187.439, "stop": 1193.526, "duration": 6.09, "cleanText": [["what", "then", "you", "have", "this", "classification", "suspect", "classification", "poverty", "v", "non", "poverty"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is that a suspect classification?", "start": 1193.526, "stop": 1195.528, "duration": 2, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "a", "suspect", "classification"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well I--", "start": 1195.528, "stop": 1195.978, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["well", "i"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "As in San Antonio v. Rodriguz?", "start": 1195.978, "stop": 1197.747, "duration": 1.77, "cleanText": [["as", "in", "san", "antonio", "v", "rodriguz"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, I took the position in my brief, and I take it now, that in social and economic policies, it perhaps is not.", "start": 1197.747, "stop": 1203.567, "duration": 5.82, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "take", "the", "position", "in", "my", "brief", "and", "i", "take", "it", "now", "that", "in", "social", "and", "economic", "policy", "it", "perhaps", "be", "not"]]}, {"text": "But involving criminal justice, it should be.", "start": 1203.567, "stop": 1206.102, "duration": 2.54, "cleanText": [["but", "involve", "criminal", "justice", "it", "should", "be"]]}, {"text": "Certainly, for the purpose of having the money and the man go scot free, such in this case, what if one of the probationers came up with the money?", "start": 1206.102, "stop": 1215.441, "duration": 9.34, "cleanText": [["certainly", "for", "the", "purpose", "of", "have", "the", "money", "and", "the", "man", "go", "scot", "free", "such", "in", "this", "case", "what", "if", "one", "of", "the", "probationer", "come", "up", "with", "the", "money"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Wood, was able to raise the money, went back into business and that's open to him, perhaps, goes back in the adult book business, gets the money, and pays his fine; he goes scot free, so to speak.", "start": 1215.441, "stop": 1226.497, "duration": 11.06, "cleanText": [["mr", "wood", "be", "able", "to", "raise", "the", "money", "go", "back", "into", "business", "and", "that", "be", "open", "to", "him", "perhaps", "go", "back", "in", "the", "adult", "book", "business", "get", "the", "money", "and", "pay", "his", "fine", "he", "go", "scot", "free", "so", "to", "speak"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well you're suggesting that paying $5,000 is not somewhat painful.", "start": 1226.497, "stop": 1232.487, "duration": 5.99, "cleanText": [["well", "you", "be", "suggest", "that", "pay", "be", "not", "somewhat", "painful"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well it's painful if you don't have it.", "start": 1232.487, "stop": 1234.403, "duration": 1.92, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "be", "painful", "if", "you", "do", "not", "have", "it"]]}, {"text": "I'm saying that if the person, they go and steal it--", "start": 1234.403, "stop": 1237.039, "duration": 2.64, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "say", "that", "if", "the", "person", "they", "go", "and", "steal", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "You mean it isn't painful if you have to go out and borrow it and put a mortgage on your house?", "start": 1237.039, "stop": 1241.759, "duration": 4.72, "cleanText": [["you", "mean", "it", "be", "not", "painful", "if", "you", "have", "to", "go", "out", "and", "borrow", "it", "and", "put", "a", "mortgage", "on", "your", "house"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It certainly is, if you have the financial resources to borrow the money.", "start": 1241.759, "stop": 1244.794, "duration": 3.04, "cleanText": [["it", "certainly", "be", "if", "you", "have", "the", "financial", "resource", "to", "borrow", "the", "money"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "If you have the house.", "start": 1244.794, "stop": 1245.744, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "have", "the", "house"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "If you have the house.", "start": 1245.744, "stop": 1246.36, "duration": 0.62, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "have", "the", "house"]]}, {"text": "If you have--", "start": 1246.36, "stop": 1246.86, "duration": 0.5, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "have"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well you're not suggesting that indigents should be free from any penalty for criminal conduct?", "start": 1246.86, "stop": 1252.131, "duration": 5.27, "cleanText": [["well", "you", "be", "not", "suggest", "that", "indigents", "should", "be", "free", "from", "any", "penalty", "for", "criminal", "conduct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Not at all; of course not.", "start": 1252.131, "stop": 1253.733, "duration": 1.6, "cleanText": [["not", "at", "all", "of", "course", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "But the consequence comes out that way, on your argument.", "start": 1253.733, "stop": 1256.868, "duration": 3.13, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "consequence", "come", "out", "that", "way", "on", "your", "argument"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 1256.868, "stop": 1257.585, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "If... if you use money as the criteria and the lack of money to go to jail.", "start": 1257.585, "stop": 1262.422, "duration": 4.84, "cleanText": [["if", "if", "you", "use", "money", "as", "the", "criterion", "and", "the", "lack", "of", "money", "to", "go", "to", "jail"]]}, {"text": "And I think we have millions of people unemployed in this country, at the present time.", "start": 1262.422, "stop": 1266.058, "duration": 3.64, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "think", "we", "have", "million", "of", "people", "unemployed", "in", "this", "country", "at", "the", "present", "time"]]}, {"text": "I think it doesn't serve any purpose, any purpose, to lock up people who do not have the money.", "start": 1266.058, "stop": 1274.48, "duration": 8.42, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "do", "not", "serve", "any", "purpose", "any", "purpose", "to", "lock", "up", "people", "who", "do", "not", "have", "the", "money"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well if these people are in fact, indigents as you suggest, putting them to work in community service instead of incarcerating them isn't going to enable them to support their families, is it?", "start": 1274.48, "stop": 1287.387, "duration": 12.91, "cleanText": [["well", "if", "these", "people", "be", "in", "fact", "indigents", "as", "you", "suggest", "put", "them", "to", "work", "in", "community", "service", "instead", "of", "incarcerate", "them", "be", "not", "go", "to", "enable", "them", "to", "support", "their", "family", "be", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what you do is, and this is just a suggestions, I mean not the only suggestion, is that if you give them community service work, perhaps on weekends, at nights... there are many ways to serve the community, and much more productive for the community for the system, help the society in which they committed the wrong; it's certainly much more noble than to just lock somebody up behind bars for 7 or 8 months because they don't have the money.", "start": 1287.387, "stop": 1314.439, "duration": 27.05, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "you", "do", "be", "and", "this", "be", "just", "a", "suggestion", "i", "mean", "not", "the", "only", "suggestion", "be", "that", "if", "you", "give", "them", "community", "service", "work", "perhaps", "on", "weekend", "at", "night", "there", "be", "many", "way", "to", "serve", "the", "community", "and", "much", "more", "productive", "for", "the", "community", "for", "the", "system", "help", "the", "society", "in", "which", "they", "commit", "the", "wrong", "it", "be", "certainly", "much", "more", "noble", "than", "to", "just", "lock", "somebody", "up", "behind", "bar", "for", "or", "month", "because", "they", "do", "not", "have", "the", "money"]]}, {"text": "This case involves, and I'm sure the judge felt, and I conceded, that a third party would pay the money.", "start": 1314.439, "stop": 1320.093, "duration": 5.65, "cleanText": [["this", "case", "involve", "and", "I", "be", "sure", "the", "judge", "felt", "and", "i", "concede", "that", "a", "third", "party", "would", "pay", "the", "money"]]}, {"text": "And it has not been forthcoming.", "start": 1320.093, "stop": 1322.461, "duration": 2.37, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "have", "not", "be", "forthcoming"]]}, {"text": "That's... obviously the judge had that basis.", "start": 1322.461, "stop": 1325.513, "duration": 3.05, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "obviously", "the", "judge", "have", "that", "basis"]]}, {"text": "This is similar in the Hunter v. Dean case, in which this case granted cert. It was a... if you remember, it was like a 10-year sentence to be placed on probation if you paid a $2,000 fine in advance.", "start": 1325.513, "stop": 1336.054, "duration": 10.54, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "similar", "in", "the", "hunter", "v", "dean", "case", "in", "which", "this", "case", "grant", "cert"], ["it", "be", "a", "if", "you", "remember", "it", "be", "like", "a", "year", "sentence", "to", "be", "place", "on", "probation", "if", "you", "pay", "a", "fine", "in", "advance"]]}, {"text": "The defendant could not... made a representation he could pay the money, he could not pay it.", "start": 1336.054, "stop": 1340.339, "duration": 4.28, "cleanText": [["the", "defendant", "could", "not", "make", "a", "representation", "he", "could", "pay", "the", "money", "he", "could", "not", "pay", "it"]]}, {"text": "And he was locked up.", "start": 1340.339, "stop": 1341.708, "duration": 1.37, "cleanText": [["and", "he", "be", "lock", "up"]]}, {"text": "And in Barnett v. Hopper, he granted cert in that case as well and vacated it as moot.", "start": 1341.708, "stop": 1345.993, "duration": 4.28, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "barnett", "v", "hopper", "he", "grant", "cert", "in", "that", "case", "as", "well", "and", "vacate", "it", "as", "moot"]]}, {"text": "Same representation was made, I can pay the money if you'll just give me probation.", "start": 1345.993, "stop": 1350.128, "duration": 4.13, "cleanText": [["same", "representation", "be", "make", "i", "can", "pay", "the", "money", "if", "you", "will", "just", "give", "me", "probation"]]}, {"text": "And the judge did and he couldn't pay the money, and the question is, do you lock people up where they don't have the money?", "start": 1350.128, "stop": 1356.468, "duration": 6.34, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "judge", "do", "and", "he", "could", "not", "pay", "the", "money", "and", "the", "question", "be", "do", "you", "lock", "people", "up", "where", "they", "do", "not", "have", "the", "money"]]}, {"text": "There should be other alternative means.", "start": 1356.468, "stop": 1359.42, "duration": 2.95, "cleanText": [["there", "should", "be", "other", "alternative", "mean"]]}, {"text": "This involves traffic cases, misdemeanors or felonies.", "start": 1359.42, "stop": 1362.538, "duration": 3.12, "cleanText": [["this", "involve", "traffic", "case", "misdemeanor", "or", "felony"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you don't question, Mr. Zell, as I understand it, that the judge, so far as the Georgia statutes went, could have imposed the prison sentence right at the outset... prison sentences, without any probation whatsoever?", "start": 1362.538, "stop": 1375.196, "duration": 12.66, "cleanText": [["but", "you", "do", "not", "question", "mr", "zell", "as", "i", "understand", "it", "that", "the", "judge", "so", "far", "as", "the", "georgia", "statutes", "go", "could", "have", "impose", "the", "prison", "sentence", "right", "at", "the", "outset", "prison", "sentence", "without", "any", "probation", "whatsoever"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 1375.196, "stop": 1375.846, "duration": 0.65, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "He made a determination they should be on probation at that point, that's correct.", "start": 1375.846, "stop": 1378.832, "duration": 2.99, "cleanText": [["he", "make", "a", "determination", "they", "should", "be", "on", "probation", "at", "that", "point", "that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well if he made a determination they should be on probation if they paid $500 a month?", "start": 1378.832, "stop": 1383.885, "duration": 5.05, "cleanText": [["well", "if", "he", "make", "a", "determination", "they", "should", "be", "on", "probation", "if", "they", "pay", "a", "month"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh no, no.", "start": 1383.885, "stop": 1384.251, "duration": 0.37, "cleanText": [["oh", "no", "no"]]}, {"text": "Well, is this--", "start": 1384.251, "stop": 1385.518, "duration": 1.27, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "this"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's a condition of the probation to be imposed?", "start": 1385.518, "stop": 1387.42, "duration": 1.9, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "a", "condition", "of", "the", "probation", "to", "be", "impose"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes.", "start": 1387.42, "stop": 1387.853, "duration": 0.43, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "They could go on probation, but they should pay $500 a month while they are on probation.", "start": 1387.853, "stop": 1392.057, "duration": 4.2, "cleanText": [["they", "could", "go", "on", "probation", "but", "they", "should", "pay", "a", "month", "while", "they", "be", "on", "probation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 1392.057, "stop": 1392.791, "duration": 0.73, "cleanText": [["right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "And if they don't pay that $500 a month, they are to go to jail.", "start": 1392.791, "stop": 1395.776, "duration": 2.99, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "they", "do", "not", "pay", "that", "a", "month", "they", "be", "to", "go", "to", "jail"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 1395.776, "stop": 1396.509, "duration": 0.73, "cleanText": [["right"]]}, {"text": "Well they will also go to jail if they don't live up to the other terms of their probation--", "start": 1396.509, "stop": 1399.678, "duration": 3.17, "cleanText": [["well", "they", "will", "also", "go", "to", "jail", "if", "they", "do", "not", "live", "up", "to", "the", "other", "term", "of", "their", "probation"]]}, {"text": "--That's right.", "start": 1399.678, "stop": 1400.195, "duration": 0.52, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}, {"text": "--even if they pay the $500.", "start": 1400.195, "stop": 1401.913, "duration": 1.72, "cleanText": [["even", "if", "they", "pay", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct, that's correct.", "start": 1401.913, "stop": 1403.147, "duration": 1.23, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "So it isn't just a condition that--", "start": 1403.147, "stop": 1404.699, "duration": 1.55, "cleanText": [["so", "it", "be", "not", "just", "a", "condition", "that"]]}, {"text": "--One of several conditions.", "start": 1404.699, "stop": 1405.999, "duration": 1.3, "cleanText": [["one", "of", "several", "condition"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right, that's... which is in the appendix, that's correct.", "start": 1405.999, "stop": 1408.282, "duration": 2.28, "cleanText": [["right", "that", "be", "which", "be", "in", "the", "appendix", "that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 1408.282, "stop": 1409.634, "duration": 1.35, "cleanText": [["right"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Zell, were there any proceedings against the employer?", "start": 1409.634, "stop": 1414.136, "duration": 4.5, "cleanText": [["mr", "zell", "we", "be", "there", "any", "proceeding", "against", "the", "employer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "In this case, no.", "start": 1414.136, "stop": 1414.855, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["in", "this", "case", "no"]]}, {"text": "There was none.", "start": 1414.855, "stop": 1415.538, "duration": 0.68, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "none"]]}, {"text": "They did not proceed against the employer.", "start": 1415.538, "stop": 1416.905, "duration": 1.37, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "not", "proceed", "against", "the", "employer"]]}, {"text": "Why, I don't remember why, I'm not sure why.", "start": 1416.905, "stop": 1419.007, "duration": 2.1, "cleanText": [["why", "i", "do", "not", "remember", "why", "I", "be", "not", "sure", "why"]]}, {"text": "It was merely against the two employees.", "start": 1419.007, "stop": 1421.275, "duration": 2.27, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "merely", "against", "the", "two", "employee"]]}, {"text": "And clearly again, the trial judge relied on the employer, frankly, I think, to pay the fines.", "start": 1421.275, "stop": 1427.595, "duration": 6.32, "cleanText": [["and", "clearly", "again", "the", "trial", "judge", "rely", "on", "the", "employer", "frankly", "i", "think", "to", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}, {"text": "And now he's not going to do it, because of change of ownership, I might add.", "start": 1427.595, "stop": 1431.647, "duration": 4.05, "cleanText": [["and", "now", "he", "be", "not", "go", "to", "do", "it", "because", "of", "change", "of", "ownership", "i", "might", "add"]]}, {"text": "He's gone now, and the money is not forthcoming.", "start": 1431.647, "stop": 1434.516, "duration": 2.87, "cleanText": [["he", "be", "go", "now", "and", "the", "money", "be", "not", "forthcoming"]]}, {"text": "And I don't see how, under Tate v. Short and Williams v. Illinois, that you could... this Court, could take the position to say that a man who doesn't have the funds goes to jail when the man or the defendant who has the funds, able to raise it through employee, employer or a friend, does not go to jail.", "start": 1434.516, "stop": 1453.73, "duration": 19.21, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "do", "not", "see", "how", "under", "tate", "v", "short", "and", "williams", "v", "illinois", "that", "you", "could", "this", "court", "could", "take", "the", "position", "to", "say", "that", "a", "man", "who", "do", "not", "have", "the", "fund", "go", "to", "jail", "when", "the", "man", "or", "the", "defendant", "who", "have", "the", "fund", "able", "to", "raise", "it", "through", "employee", "employer", "or", "a", "friend", "do", "not", "go", "to", "jail"]]}, {"text": "How do you square this case with Tate case and the Williams case?", "start": 1453.73, "stop": 1458.548, "duration": 4.82, "cleanText": [["how", "do", "you", "square", "this", "case", "with", "tate", "case", "and", "the", "williams", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yet, you concede that the judge could have sentenced them ab initio, to twelve months?", "start": 1458.548, "stop": 1467.071, "duration": 8.52, "cleanText": [["yet", "you", "concede", "that", "the", "judge", "could", "have", "sentence", "them", "ab", "initio", "to", "twelve", "month"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "In the very beginning.", "start": 1467.071, "stop": 1467.704, "duration": 0.63, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "very", "beginning"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1467.704, "stop": 1468.388, "duration": 0.68, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct, that's correct.", "start": 1468.388, "stop": 1469.59, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "He felt that they were good subjects, fit subjects, to be on probation.", "start": 1469.59, "stop": 1473.642, "duration": 4.05, "cleanText": [["he", "felt", "that", "they", "we", "be", "good", "subject", "fit", "subject", "to", "be", "on", "probation"]]}, {"text": "That they should not be incarcerated... he made that determination.", "start": 1473.642, "stop": 1477.345, "duration": 3.7, "cleanText": [["that", "they", "should", "not", "be", "incarcerate", "he", "make", "that", "determination"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well but isn't that a typical determination with a case of non violent, first or second offenders?", "start": 1477.345, "stop": 1486.634, "duration": 9.29, "cleanText": [["well", "but", "be", "not", "that", "a", "typical", "determination", "with", "a", "case", "of", "non", "violent", "first", "or", "second", "offender"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Generally speaking, I would say so, yes.", "start": 1486.634, "stop": 1488.201, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["generally", "speak", "i", "would", "say", "so", "yes"]]}, {"text": "The... I might add that the American Bar Association of Standards relating to sentencing suggests... I mean, the judge imposes a sentence,... that he look at the profitability in the crime, non violent crime, but it also suggests, American Bar Association, that they not revoke the man's probation if he doesn't have the ability to pay the fine.", "start": 1488.201, "stop": 1508.965, "duration": 20.76, "cleanText": [["the", "i", "might", "add", "that", "the", "american", "bar", "association", "of", "standard", "relate", "to", "sentence", "suggests", "i", "mean", "the", "judge", "impose", "a", "sentence", "that", "he", "look", "at", "the", "profitability", "in", "the", "crime", "non", "violent", "crime", "but", "it", "also", "suggest", "american", "bar", "association", "that", "they", "not", "revoke", "the", "man", "s", "probation", "if", "he", "do", "not", "have", "the", "ability", "to", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}, {"text": "And in all law review articles I've read, and all the cases I could find, there's not one case except in Georgia as far as I know in Shepherdizing Tate and Williams, where a court has said if you don't have the money on the installment basis, you go to jail.", "start": 1508.965, "stop": 1523.54, "duration": 14.58, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "all", "law", "review", "article", "I", "have", "read", "and", "all", "the", "case", "i", "could", "find", "there", "be", "not", "one", "case", "except", "in", "georgia", "as", "far", "as", "i", "know", "in", "shepherdizing", "tate", "and", "williams", "where", "a", "court", "have", "say", "if", "you", "do", "not", "have", "the", "money", "on", "the", "installment", "basis", "you", "go", "to", "jail"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would you... what if the judge had said this,", "start": 1523.54, "stop": 1528.111, "duration": 4.57, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "what", "if", "the", "judge", "have", "say", "this"]]}, {"text": "\"well I'm sentencing you to a year in jail, but I'm going to put you on probation subject to normal probation conditions and I'm also going to fine you $5,000, payable in installments and if you fail to pay the installments, you go to jail for ten days. \"", "start": 1528.111, "stop": 1548.775, "duration": 20.66, "cleanText": [["well", "I", "be", "sentence", "you", "to", "a", "year", "in", "jail", "but", "I", "be", "go", "to", "put", "you", "on", "probation", "subject", "to", "normal", "probation", "condition", "and", "I", "be", "also", "go", "to", "fine", "you", "payable", "in", "installment", "and", "if", "you", "fail", "to", "pay", "the", "installment", "you", "go", "to", "jail", "for", "ten", "days"]]}, {"text": "That's a separate, I must have some way of... something to take the place of the fine, but I'll just send you to jail for ten days if you don't pay the fine.", "start": 1548.775, "stop": 1563.95, "duration": 15.17, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "a", "separate", "i", "must", "have", "some", "way", "of", "something", "to", "take", "the", "place", "of", "the", "fine", "but", "I", "will", "just", "send", "you", "to", "jail", "for", "ten", "day", "if", "you", "do", "not", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}, {"text": "But of course you are subject to going to jail for a year if you don't live up to the conditions of your probation.", "start": 1563.95, "stop": 1572.204, "duration": 8.25, "cleanText": [["but", "of", "course", "you", "be", "subject", "to", "go", "to", "jail", "for", "a", "year", "if", "you", "do", "not", "live", "up", "to", "the", "condition", "of", "your", "probation"]]}, {"text": "Would you be here then?", "start": 1572.204, "stop": 1574.123, "duration": 1.92, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "be", "here", "then"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think so, yes.", "start": 1574.123, "stop": 1575.425, "duration": 1.3, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "so", "yes"]]}, {"text": "I don't think a man should serve one day in jail based on his wealth.", "start": 1575.425, "stop": 1579.394, "duration": 3.97, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "a", "man", "should", "serve", "one", "day", "in", "jail", "base", "on", "his", "wealth"]]}, {"text": "I think that's... should be a suspect category, if it isn't already under Griffin v. Illinois case.", "start": 1579.394, "stop": 1583.929, "duration": 4.54, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "be", "should", "be", "a", "suspect", "category", "if", "it", "be", "not", "already", "under", "griffin", "v", "illinois", "case"]]}, {"text": "And I think that that should be a criteria.", "start": 1583.929, "stop": 1585.548, "duration": 1.62, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "think", "that", "that", "should", "be", "a", "criterion"]]}, {"text": "It serves no purpose to either raise revenue, punish the defendant... because he sits in jail knowing that if he had the money, he'd be out, while other defendants and other clients I've had, have paid the fine and are not sitting in jail.", "start": 1585.548, "stop": 1597.838, "duration": 12.29, "cleanText": [["it", "serve", "no", "purpose", "to", "either", "raise", "revenue", "punish", "the", "defendant", "because", "he", "sit", "in", "jail", "knowing", "that", "if", "he", "have", "the", "money", "he", "would", "be", "out", "while", "other", "defendant", "and", "other", "client", "I", "have", "have", "have", "pay", "the", "fine", "and", "be", "not", "sit", "in", "jail"]]}, {"text": "I think it causes--", "start": 1597.838, "stop": 1598.957, "duration": 1.12, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "cause"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Are you saying that all criminal statutes that says 30 days or $100 are unconstitutional?", "start": 1598.957, "stop": 1608.163, "duration": 9.21, "cleanText": [["be", "you", "say", "that", "all", "criminal", "statute", "that", "say", "day", "or", "be", "unconstitutional"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Under your decisions, yes.", "start": 1608.163, "stop": 1609.363, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["under", "your", "decision", "yes"]]}, {"text": "If you don't have the money.", "start": 1609.363, "stop": 1610.363, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "do", "not", "have", "the", "money"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't know whether that's true or not; I don't think we've held that, yet.", "start": 1610.363, "stop": 1614.567, "duration": 4.2, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know", "whether", "that", "be", "true", "or", "not", "i", "do", "not", "think", "we", "have", "hold", "that", "yet"]]}, {"text": "We've specially reserved it.", "start": 1614.567, "stop": 1616.25, "duration": 1.68, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "specially", "reserve", "it"]]}, {"text": "And... but that's your... then your submission is that... that $100 or one day is bad?", "start": 1616.25, "stop": 1625.525, "duration": 9.28, "cleanText": [["and", "but", "that", "be", "your", "then", "your", "submission", "be", "that", "that", "or", "one", "day", "be", "bad"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 1625.525, "stop": 1626.025, "duration": 0.5, "cleanText": [["no"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "What?", "start": 1626.025, "stop": 1626.958, "duration": 0.93, "cleanText": [["what"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Only if the individual does not have the funds--", "start": 1626.958, "stop": 1631.679, "duration": 4.72, "cleanText": [["only", "if", "the", "individual", "do", "not", "have", "the", "fund"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "All right, but that's bad to apply any indigent?", "start": 1631.679, "stop": 1636.481, "duration": 4.8, "cleanText": [["all", "right", "but", "that", "be", "bad", "to", "apply", "any", "indigent"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, or a person who has not squandered the money away, has not been negligent, willful; that seems to be the federal... at least in the circuit, I'm from the Fifth Circuit, and the Fourth Circuit, where they've reached that issue.", "start": 1636.481, "stop": 1648.721, "duration": 12.24, "cleanText": [["yes", "or", "a", "person", "who", "have", "not", "squander", "the", "money", "away", "have", "not", "be", "negligent", "willful", "that", "seem", "to", "be", "the", "federal", "at", "least", "in", "the", "circuit", "I", "be", "from", "the", "fifth", "circuit", "and", "the", "fourth", "circuit", "where", "they", "have", "reach", "that", "issue"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "What if he squandered the money, what difference does that make?", "start": 1648.721, "stop": 1652.675, "duration": 3.95, "cleanText": [["what", "if", "he", "squander", "the", "money", "what", "difference", "do", "that", "make"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think then the Court, such as in a... I'm using an analogy as in a divorce rule, in a man supporting his family.", "start": 1652.675, "stop": 1660.029, "duration": 7.35, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "then", "the", "court", "such", "as", "in", "a"], ["I", "be", "use", "an", "analogy", "as", "in", "a", "divorce", "rule", "in", "a", "man", "support", "his", "family"]]}, {"text": "If he squanders away money that he didn't give to his family, he could be held in contempt of Court.", "start": 1660.029, "stop": 1664.833, "duration": 4.8, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "squander", "away", "money", "that", "he", "do", "not", "give", "to", "his", "family", "he", "could", "be", "hold", "in", "contempt", "of", "court"]]}, {"text": "And I think this would be similar.", "start": 1664.833, "stop": 1666.366, "duration": 1.53, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "think", "this", "would", "be", "similar"]]}, {"text": "If he squandered the money away or had a good job that he turned down, to make a lot of money, willfully didn't work, I think then the Court can use that as a criteria to revoke him, put him in jail.", "start": 1666.366, "stop": 1678.491, "duration": 12.13, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "squander", "the", "money", "away", "or", "have", "a", "good", "job", "that", "he", "turn", "down", "to", "make", "a", "lot", "of", "money", "willfully", "do", "not", "work", "i", "think", "then", "the", "court", "can", "use", "that", "as", "a", "criterion", "to", "revoke", "him", "put", "him", "in", "jail"]]}, {"text": "Because he's not trying under the probation, under his probation, to pay the fine.", "start": 1678.491, "stop": 1683.977, "duration": 5.49, "cleanText": [["because", "he", "be", "not", "try", "under", "the", "probation", "under", "his", "probation", "to", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "And you think it's the function of this Court to evaluate considerations of that kind?", "start": 1683.977, "stop": 1689.948, "duration": 5.97, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "think", "it", "be", "the", "function", "of", "this", "court", "to", "evaluate", "consideration", "of", "that", "kind"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, it's the trial judge.", "start": 1689.948, "stop": 1691.317, "duration": 1.37, "cleanText": [["no", "it", "be", "the", "trial", "judge"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "But the, we... if you say it's a consideration there, you're, by implication, saying we must pass on that sometime.", "start": 1691.317, "stop": 1701.623, "duration": 10.31, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "we", "if", "you", "say", "it", "be", "a", "consideration", "there", "you", "be", "by", "implication", "say", "we", "must", "pass", "on", "that", "sometime"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well certainly--", "start": 1701.623, "stop": 1702.875, "duration": 1.25, "cleanText": [["well", "certainly"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "And you said this was a constitutional issue.", "start": 1702.875, "stop": 1705.227, "duration": 2.35, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "say", "this", "be", "a", "constitutional", "issue"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Certainly.", "start": 1705.227, "stop": 1706.143, "duration": 0.92, "cleanText": [["certainly"]]}, {"text": "If a man is incarcerated, no question about it; if he's incarcerated, and there's no evidence to put him in jail, I think a writ of habeas corpus would lie.", "start": 1706.143, "stop": 1713.664, "duration": 7.52, "cleanText": [["if", "a", "man", "be", "incarcerate", "no", "question", "about", "it", "if", "he", "be", "incarcerate", "and", "there", "be", "no", "evidence", "to", "put", "him", "in", "jail", "i", "think", "a", "writ", "of", "habeas", "corpus", "would", "lie"]]}, {"text": "If a man is put in jail for no reason, whether it be he has no funds or for whatever reason, the judge thought he ought to go to jail for no reason, he just didn't like the way... his hair was too long... I had a case like that recently, where the judge revoked a man's probation because his hair was too long.", "start": 1713.664, "stop": 1727.74, "duration": 14.08, "cleanText": [["if", "a", "man", "be", "put", "in", "jail", "for", "no", "reason", "whether", "it", "be", "he", "have", "no", "fund", "or", "for", "whatever", "reason", "the", "judge", "think", "he", "ought", "to", "go", "to", "jail", "for", "no", "reason", "he", "just", "do", "not", "like", "the", "way", "his", "hair", "be", "too", "long", "i", "have", "a", "case", "like", "that", "recently", "where", "the", "judge", "revoke", "a", "man", "s", "probation", "because", "his", "hair", "be", "too", "long"]]}, {"text": "And I think I luckily reversed that in the state courts.", "start": 1727.74, "stop": 1730.358, "duration": 2.62, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "think", "i", "luckily", "reverse", "that", "in", "the", "state", "court"]]}, {"text": "But, a writ would lie... you can't lock a man up for no reason.", "start": 1730.358, "stop": 1733.994, "duration": 3.64, "cleanText": [["but", "a", "writ", "would", "lie", "you", "can", "not", "lock", "a", "man", "up", "for", "no", "reason"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well what if a man were convicted of first degree murder and had no funds?", "start": 1733.994, "stop": 1740.414, "duration": 6.42, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "if", "a", "man", "we", "be", "convict", "of", "first", "degree", "murder", "and", "have", "no", "fund"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1740.414, "stop": 1740.733, "duration": 0.32, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would you say he couldn't go to jail?", "start": 1740.733, "stop": 1743.016, "duration": 2.28, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "say", "he", "could", "not", "go", "to", "jail"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "You mean if... well, of course, in Georgia if you are convicted of first degree murder, you must either get a life or death sentence.", "start": 1743.016, "stop": 1749.839, "duration": 6.82, "cleanText": [["you", "mean", "if", "well", "of", "course", "in", "georgia", "if", "you", "be", "convict", "of", "first", "degree", "murder", "you", "must", "either", "get", "a", "life", "or", "death", "sentence"]]}, {"text": "I'm only talking about where you're placed on probation or given a some kind of a suspended sentence and you use wealth, money, as the criteria to lock him up.", "start": 1749.839, "stop": 1758.794, "duration": 8.96, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "only", "talk", "about", "where", "you", "be", "place", "on", "probation", "or", "give", "a", "some", "kind", "of", "a", "suspended", "sentence", "and", "you", "use", "wealth", "money", "as", "the", "criterion", "to", "lock", "him", "up"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "But it isn't part of the trial judge's reasoning that you want to put as few people in jail as possible.", "start": 1758.794, "stop": 1765.631, "duration": 6.84, "cleanText": [["but", "it", "be", "not", "part", "of", "the", "trial", "judge", "s", "reasoning", "that", "you", "want", "to", "put", "as", "few", "people", "in", "jail", "as", "possible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 1765.631, "stop": 1766.431, "duration": 0.8, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "And if he knew that you couldn't--", "start": 1766.431, "stop": 1771.916, "duration": 5.48, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "he", "know", "that", "you", "could", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Collect the fine?", "start": 1771.916, "stop": 1772.668, "duration": 0.75, "cleanText": [["collect", "the", "fine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "--collect the fine or put him in jail, he... he probably would sentence him to jail in the first place.", "start": 1772.668, "stop": 1779.505, "duration": 6.84, "cleanText": [["collect", "the", "fine", "or", "put", "him", "in", "jail", "he", "he", "probably", "would", "sentence", "him", "to", "jail", "in", "the", "first", "place"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I'm going to take it from a theoretical point of view, if I may.", "start": 1779.505, "stop": 1782.391, "duration": 2.89, "cleanText": [["well", "I", "be", "go", "to", "take", "it", "from", "a", "theoretical", "point", "of", "view", "if", "i", "may"]]}, {"text": "I'd like to think that trial judges will make a determination... and I think they are duty bound to do this... whether a man should go to jail or not, regardless of money, regardless of other criteria, where in the first instance should he put him out on the street, serve his sentence in society, first.", "start": 1782.391, "stop": 1803.287, "duration": 20.9, "cleanText": [["I", "would", "like", "to", "think", "that", "trial", "judge", "will", "make", "a", "determination", "and", "i", "think", "they", "be", "duty", "bound", "to", "do", "this", "whether", "a", "man", "should", "go", "to", "jail", "or", "not", "regardless", "of", "money", "regardless", "of", "other", "criterion", "where", "in", "the", "first", "instance", "should", "he", "put", "him", "out", "on", "the", "street", "serve", "his", "sentence", "in", "society", "first"]]}, {"text": "If he makes that determination as he did in this case, he then decides what other penalties to impose upon the Defendant, such as a fine, community service, weekends in jail, what other... myriad amount of things he could use to so to speak punish the man.", "start": 1803.287, "stop": 1823.184, "duration": 19.9, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "make", "that", "determination", "as", "he", "do", "in", "this", "case", "he", "then", "decide", "what", "other", "penalty", "to", "impose", "upon", "the", "defendant", "such", "as", "a", "fine", "community", "service", "weekend", "in", "jail", "what", "other", "myriad", "amount", "of", "thing", "he", "could", "use", "to", "so", "to", "speak", "punish", "the", "man"]]}, {"text": "Well, not punish him, but make him helpful to the community.", "start": 1823.184, "stop": 1826.236, "duration": 3.05, "cleanText": [["well", "not", "punish", "him", "but", "make", "him", "helpful", "to", "the", "community"]]}, {"text": "Primarily I'd consider community service work would be the best thing to do with people who don't have funds.", "start": 1826.236, "stop": 1831.956, "duration": 5.72, "cleanText": [["primarily", "I", "would", "consider", "community", "service", "work", "would", "be", "the", "best", "thing", "to", "do", "with", "people", "who", "do", "not", "have", "fund"]]}, {"text": "That helps himself, he pays a penalty, he loses his recreational time on weekends and at nights, and he also helps the community by doing some charitable work.", "start": 1831.956, "stop": 1840.662, "duration": 8.71, "cleanText": [["that", "help", "himself", "he", "pay", "a", "penalty", "he", "lose", "his", "recreational", "time", "on", "weekend", "and", "at", "night", "and", "he", "also", "help", "the", "community", "by", "do", "some", "charitable", "work"]]}, {"text": "What is the purpose of collecting this money?", "start": 1840.662, "stop": 1843.364, "duration": 2.7, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "the", "purpose", "of", "collect", "this", "money"]]}, {"text": "Are we saying the government doesn't have the money to run itself?", "start": 1843.364, "stop": 1845.897, "duration": 2.53, "cleanText": [["be", "we", "say", "the", "government", "do", "not", "have", "the", "money", "to", "run", "itself"]]}, {"text": "Is this a revenue producing measure?", "start": 1845.897, "stop": 1847.966, "duration": 2.07, "cleanText": [["be", "this", "a", "revenue", "produce", "measure"]]}, {"text": "Or what are we furthering by saying you pay this money, it's important in the system of criminal justice.", "start": 1847.966, "stop": 1854.737, "duration": 6.77, "cleanText": [["or", "what", "be", "we", "further", "by", "say", "you", "pay", "this", "money", "it", "be", "important", "in", "the", "system", "of", "criminal", "justice"]]}, {"text": "It isn't important; it's very unimportant to collect money.", "start": 1854.737, "stop": 1857.172, "duration": 2.43, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "important", "it", "be", "very", "unimportant", "to", "collect", "money"]]}, {"text": "And the judges, trial judges should realize this and I think most of them do, frankly.", "start": 1857.172, "stop": 1861.409, "duration": 4.24, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "judge", "trial", "judge", "should", "realize", "this", "and", "i", "think", "most", "of", "them", "do", "frankly"]]}, {"text": "And to use money as a criteria to put a man in jail among murderers perhaps... and he sits in jail and he says golly, my friend paid the fine and I can't.", "start": 1861.409, "stop": 1872.783, "duration": 11.37, "cleanText": [["and", "to", "use", "money", "as", "a", "criterion", "to", "put", "a", "man", "in", "jail", "among", "murderer", "perhaps", "and", "he", "sit", "in", "jail", "and", "he", "say", "golly", "my", "friend", "pay", "the", "fine", "and", "i", "can", "not"]]}, {"text": "And he goes free because he had money.", "start": 1872.783, "stop": 1875.05, "duration": 2.27, "cleanText": [["and", "he", "go", "free", "because", "he", "have", "money"]]}, {"text": "I think this is a discredit to our system of justice and it should not be allowed, and I think you should follow the Tate and Williams case, this Court should, and did not permit this.", "start": 1875.05, "stop": 1885.524, "duration": 10.47, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "this", "be", "a", "discredit", "to", "our", "system", "of", "justice", "and", "it", "should", "not", "be", "allow", "and", "i", "think", "you", "should", "follow", "the", "tate", "and", "williams", "case", "this", "court", "should", "and", "do", "not", "permit", "this"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well what it comes down to is to find a punishment that is available for imposition on him and I suppose some people, due to circumstances, are free from any punishment except going to jail.", "start": 1885.524, "stop": 1901.051, "duration": 15.53, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "it", "come", "down", "to", "be", "to", "find", "a", "punishment", "that", "be", "available", "for", "imposition", "on", "him", "and", "i", "suppose", "some", "people", "due", "to", "circumstance", "be", "free", "from", "any", "punishment", "except", "go", "to", "jail"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Free from paying money.", "start": 1901.051, "stop": 1902.886, "duration": 1.84, "cleanText": [["free", "from", "pay", "money"]]}, {"text": "First of all, most defendants violate the law because they don't have money, obviously; poverty, I'm sure causes a lot a crime, I don't think there's any question about it.", "start": 1902.886, "stop": 1909.889, "duration": 7, "cleanText": [["first", "of", "all", "most", "defendant", "violate", "the", "law", "because", "they", "do", "not", "have", "money", "obviously", "poverty", "I", "be", "sure", "cause", "a", "lot", "a", "crime", "i", "do", "not", "think", "there", "be", "any", "question", "about", "it"]]}, {"text": "And so most defendants are broke and have no money.", "start": 1909.889, "stop": 1912.508, "duration": 2.62, "cleanText": [["and", "so", "most", "defendant", "be", "break", "and", "have", "no", "money"]]}, {"text": "So the imposition of fines on people who are broke or poor or have no money, who have robbed or stolen to get money, it's just inconsistent.", "start": 1912.508, "stop": 1919.595, "duration": 7.09, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "imposition", "of", "fine", "on", "people", "who", "be", "break", "or", "poor", "or", "have", "no", "money", "who", "have", "rob", "or", "steal", "to", "get", "money", "it", "be", "just", "inconsistent"]]}, {"text": "You're just catching yourself going around in circles.", "start": 1919.595, "stop": 1921.881, "duration": 2.29, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "just", "catch", "yourself", "go", "around", "in", "circle"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would you object if the Court had a hearing to find out if this man could pay $10.00 a week?", "start": 1921.881, "stop": 1927.918, "duration": 6.04, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "object", "if", "the", "court", "have", "a", "hearing", "to", "find", "out", "if", "this", "man", "could", "pay", "a", "week"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Not at all.", "start": 1927.918, "stop": 1929.037, "duration": 1.12, "cleanText": [["not", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "In fact,--", "start": 1929.037, "stop": 1929.603, "duration": 0.57, "cleanText": [["in", "fact"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well I thought so, but you weren't saying it right then.", "start": 1929.603, "stop": 1932.672, "duration": 3.07, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "so", "but", "you", "be", "not", "say", "it", "right", "then"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That's correct.", "start": 1932.672, "stop": 1933.189, "duration": 0.52, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "Well--", "start": 1933.189, "stop": 1934.472, "duration": 1.28, "cleanText": [["well"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "All right.", "start": 1934.472, "stop": 1935.574, "duration": 1.1, "cleanText": [["all", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--In fact I asked the judge, I said look judge, reduce the fine, let's make it commensurate.", "start": 1935.574, "stop": 1940.126, "duration": 4.55, "cleanText": [["in", "fact", "i", "ask", "the", "judge", "i", "say", "look", "judge", "reduce", "the", "fine", "let", "us", "make", "it", "commensurate"]]}, {"text": "This is a... failure to pay as directed, $500 a month.", "start": 1940.126, "stop": 1945.413, "duration": 5.29, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "a", "failure", "to", "pay", "as", "direct", "a", "month"]]}, {"text": "There's nothing with the judge saying, well, I misread this, I thought you could pay $500... I'll reduce it to $10.00 a month, which may be as much to this individual defendant as $1,000 a week would be to some other defendants who are perhaps involved in a Waco conviction... organized crime conviction.", "start": 1945.413, "stop": 1961.674, "duration": 16.26, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "nothing", "with", "the", "judge", "say", "well", "i", "misread", "this", "i", "think", "you", "could", "pay"], ["I", "will", "reduce", "it", "to", "a", "month", "which", "may", "be", "as", "much", "to", "this", "individual", "defendant", "as", "a", "week", "would", "be", "to", "some", "other", "defendant", "who", "be", "perhaps", "involve", "in", "a", "waco", "conviction", "organize", "crime", "conviction"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your time is up.", "start": 1961.674, "stop": 1962.324, "duration": 0.65, "cleanText": [["your", "time", "be", "up"]]}, {"text": "But just one question, at least from me.", "start": 1962.324, "stop": 1964.876, "duration": 2.55, "cleanText": [["but", "just", "one", "question", "at", "least", "from", "me"]]}, {"text": "Pursuing Justice Blackmun's question, could the judge under Georgia law have said, I will consider probation if you will post a bond to guarantee the payment of your fine over a period of time, as a guarantee for these installments.", "start": 1964.876, "stop": 1979.72, "duration": 14.84, "cleanText": [["pursue", "justice", "blackmun", "s", "question", "could", "the", "judge", "under", "georgia", "law", "have", "say", "i", "will", "consider", "probation", "if", "you", "will", "post", "a", "bond", "to", "guarantee", "the", "payment", "of", "your", "fine", "over", "a", "period", "of", "time", "as", "a", "guarantee", "for", "these", "installment"]]}, {"text": "Would that be permitted under Georgia law?", "start": 1979.72, "stop": 1982.338, "duration": 2.62, "cleanText": [["would", "that", "be", "permit", "under", "georgia", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't think so.", "start": 1982.338, "stop": 1983.038, "duration": 0.7, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "so"]]}, {"text": "I think the sentence clearly reads as sentence or fine or both and I don't think it's permissible.", "start": 1983.038, "stop": 1986.94, "duration": 3.9, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "the", "sentence", "clearly", "read", "as", "sentence", "or", "fine", "or", "both", "and", "i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "be", "permissible"]]}, {"text": "But again, it's to bar... based on his wealth, to post the money, needed money.", "start": 1986.94, "stop": 1990.943, "duration": 4, "cleanText": [["but", "again", "it", "be", "to", "bar", "base", "on", "his", "wealth", "to", "post", "the", "money", "need", "money"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Zell, let me ask you one more question.", "start": 1990.943, "stop": 1993.729, "duration": 2.79, "cleanText": [["mr", "zell", "let", "me", "ask", "you", "one", "more", "question"]]}, {"text": "So, supposing that an armed robber, convicted of armed robbery, came before the judge for sentencing.", "start": 1993.729, "stop": 2002.183, "duration": 8.45, "cleanText": [["so", "suppose", "that", "an", "armed", "robber", "convict", "of", "armed", "robbery", "come", "before", "the", "judge", "for", "sentence"]]}, {"text": "Under your going around in lcircles argument, would it be a constitutional defense for him to say I just didn't have any money, I couldn't get a job and so I just had to commit this armed robbery?", "start": 2002.183, "stop": 2017.093, "duration": 14.91, "cleanText": [["under", "your", "go", "around", "in", "lcircles", "argument", "would", "it", "be", "a", "constitutional", "defense", "for", "him", "to", "say", "i", "just", "do", "not", "have", "any", "money", "i", "could", "not", "get", "a", "job", "and", "so", "i", "just", "have", "to", "commit", "this", "arm", "robbery"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sure many defendants have said that to the trial judge; I certainly wouldn't advise this Court that I was represented to say that.", "start": 2017.093, "stop": 2023.08, "duration": 5.99, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sure", "many", "defendant", "have", "say", "that", "to", "the", "trial", "judge", "i", "certainly", "would", "not", "advise", "this", "court", "that", "i", "be", "represent", "to", "say", "that"]]}, {"text": "All we're saying is that after the judge makes a determination that he could be on the street, that he could be on probation, and he has a suspended sentence; don't lock him up later for not having wealth, not having material goods.", "start": 2023.08, "stop": 2036.739, "duration": 13.66, "cleanText": [["all", "we", "be", "say", "be", "that", "after", "the", "judge", "make", "a", "determination", "that", "he", "could", "be", "on", "the", "street", "that", "he", "could", "be", "on", "probation", "and", "he", "have", "a", "suspended", "sentence", "do", "not", "lock", "him", "up", "later", "for", "not", "have", "wealth", "not", "have", "material", "good"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Zell, I don't want to repeat myself, but the determination that the sentencing judge made was that he would continue him on probation so long as he paid $10.00 per month.", "start": 2036.739, "stop": 2048.58, "duration": 11.84, "cleanText": [["mr", "zell", "i", "do", "not", "want", "to", "repeat", "myself", "but", "the", "determination", "that", "the", "sentencing", "judge", "make", "be", "that", "he", "would", "continue", "him", "on", "probation", "so", "long", "as", "he", "pay", "per", "month"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think--", "start": 2048.58, "stop": 2049.03, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["i", "think"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "It wasn't an unconditional determination.", "start": 2049.03, "stop": 2051.016, "duration": 1.99, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "an", "unconditional", "determination"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, it was conditioned on paying the money, that's correct.", "start": 2051.016, "stop": 2052.934, "duration": 1.92, "cleanText": [["no", "it", "be", "condition", "on", "pay", "the", "money", "that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Among other conditions?", "start": 2052.934, "stop": 2053.984, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["among", "other", "condition"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 2053.984, "stop": 2054.518, "duration": 0.53, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "It was conditioned on his wealth, on money, and he could not... he reached the other other conditions of probation, there were about ten of them in the record.", "start": 2054.518, "stop": 2062.39, "duration": 7.87, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "condition", "on", "his", "wealth", "on", "money", "and", "he", "could", "not", "he", "reach", "the", "other", "other", "condition", "of", "probation", "there", "we", "be", "about", "ten", "of", "them", "in", "the", "record"]]}, {"text": "But the condition he couldn't reach was the wealth, the money condition, and that shouldn't be a criteria or reason to lock a man up.", "start": 2062.39, "stop": 2069.494, "duration": 7.1, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "condition", "he", "could", "not", "reach", "be", "the", "wealth", "the", "money", "condition", "and", "that", "should", "not", "be", "a", "criterion", "or", "reason", "to", "lock", "a", "man", "up"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "And other people who could satisfy that condition, but... and who could satisfy all the conditions stayed out of jail?", "start": 2069.494, "stop": 2078.249, "duration": 8.75, "cleanText": [["and", "other", "people", "who", "could", "satisfy", "that", "condition", "but", "and", "who", "could", "satisfy", "all", "the", "condition", "stay", "out", "of", "jail"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "Who could pay the money, could stay out of jail.", "start": 2078.249, "stop": 2080.201, "duration": 1.95, "cleanText": [["who", "could", "pay", "the", "money", "could", "stay", "out", "of", "jail"]]}, {"text": "And if the Court determines that... that this man paid the money and stayed out... then that would be a reverse discrimination, then the Courts say well maybe they could do some community service work, put in a lot of hours, some of your time is worth the minimum wage, $3.00 an hour, and work on weekends or at nights, working this fine off in the community.", "start": 2080.201, "stop": 2098.297, "duration": 18.1, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "the", "court", "determine", "that", "that", "this", "man", "pay", "the", "money", "and", "stay", "out", "then", "that", "would", "be", "a", "reverse", "discrimination", "then", "the", "court", "say", "well", "maybe", "they", "could", "do", "some", "community", "service", "work", "put", "in", "a", "lot", "of", "hour", "some", "of", "your", "time", "be", "worth", "the", "minimum", "wage", "an", "hour", "and", "work", "on", "weekend", "or", "at", "night", "work", "this", "fine", "off", "in", "the", "community"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well as one of my colleagues noted, it isn't our business to try to write Georgia's statute on that subject.", "start": 2098.297, "stop": 2104.834, "duration": 6.54, "cleanText": [["well", "as", "one", "of", "my", "colleague", "note", "it", "be", "not", "our", "business", "to", "try", "to", "write", "georgia", "s", "statute", "on", "that", "subject"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Glenn Zell", "textObjs": [{"text": "But certainly it's available to the judge under Georgia law.", "start": 2104.834, "stop": 2107.753, "duration": 2.92, "cleanText": [["but", "certainly", "it", "be", "available", "to", "the", "judge", "under", "georgia", "law"]]}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 2107.753, "stop": 2108.786, "duration": 1.03, "cleanText": [["thank", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Dunsmore.", "start": 2108.786, "stop": 2112.639, "duration": 3.85, "cleanText": [["mr", "dunsmore"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court:", "start": 2112.639, "stop": 2116.191, "duration": 3.55, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "The issue in this case is whether a judge can condition probation on the payment of a fine, revoke that period of probation for non payment of the fine, particularly when the individual has represented to the Court that they had the funds or the means by which to pay the fine.", "start": 2116.191, "stop": 2136.955, "duration": 20.76, "cleanText": [["the", "issue", "in", "this", "case", "be", "whether", "a", "judge", "can", "condition", "probation", "on", "the", "payment", "of", "a", "fine", "revoke", "that", "period", "of", "probation", "for", "non", "payment", "of", "the", "fine", "particularly", "when", "the", "individual", "have", "represent", "to", "the", "court", "that", "they", "have", "the", "fund", "or", "the", "mean", "by", "which", "to", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}, {"text": "Underlying that consideration is whether the sentencing judge could properly consider third party sources as assisting the individual in the payment of the fine.", "start": 2136.955, "stop": 2149.43, "duration": 12.47, "cleanText": [["underlie", "that", "consideration", "be", "whether", "the", "sentencing", "judge", "could", "properly", "consider", "third", "party", "source", "as", "assist", "the", "individual", "in", "the", "payment", "of", "the", "fine"]]}, {"text": "Now this case does not involve, as some cases previously to the Court have provided, extending the period of confinement greater than allowed by statute.", "start": 2149.43, "stop": 2160.22, "duration": 10.79, "cleanText": [["now", "this", "case", "do", "not", "involve", "as", "some", "case", "previously", "to", "the", "court", "have", "provide", "extend", "the", "period", "of", "confinement", "great", "than", "allow", "by", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Attorney General, suppose a man has got the money and he is sentenced to pay $5,000 a month, which is no problem to him.", "start": 2160.22, "stop": 2172.861, "duration": 12.64, "cleanText": [["mr", "attorney", "general", "suppose", "a", "man", "have", "get", "the", "money", "and", "he", "be", "sentence", "to", "pay", "a", "month", "which", "be", "no", "problem", "to", "him"]]}, {"text": "But he starts serving the sentence at the end of the year 1929 and he is caught along with everybody else.", "start": 2172.861, "stop": 2182.251, "duration": 9.39, "cleanText": [["but", "he", "start", "serve", "the", "sentence", "at", "the", "end", "of", "the", "year", "and", "he", "be", "catch", "along", "with", "everybody", "else"]]}, {"text": "In Georgia, what happens?", "start": 2182.251, "stop": 2184.536, "duration": 2.28, "cleanText": [["in", "georgia", "what", "happen"]]}, {"text": "Is there any relief for him?", "start": 2184.536, "stop": 2186.705, "duration": 2.17, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "any", "relief", "for", "him"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, he can always go through it in Georgia, at any time, the Courts... we pointed that out in the footnotes, the Court always has the inherent power to modify a sentence or to release the individual from the conditions of his probation at that time.", "start": 2186.705, "stop": 2203.482, "duration": 16.78, "cleanText": [["yes", "he", "can", "always", "go", "through", "it", "in", "georgia", "at", "any", "time", "the", "court", "we", "point", "that", "out", "in", "the", "footnote", "the", "court", "always", "have", "the", "inherent", "power", "to", "modify", "a", "sentence", "or", "to", "release", "the", "individual", "from", "the", "condition", "of", "his", "probation", "at", "that", "time"]]}, {"text": "Normal procedure as to what percentage of the cases, I could not indicate to you, but that is a means available to a defendant.", "start": 2203.482, "stop": 2212.003, "duration": 8.52, "cleanText": [["normal", "procedure", "as", "to", "what", "percentage", "of", "the", "case", "i", "could", "not", "indicate", "to", "you", "but", "that", "be", "a", "mean", "available", "to", "a", "defendant"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "You go to the sentencing judge?", "start": 2212.003, "stop": 2213.872, "duration": 1.87, "cleanText": [["you", "go", "to", "the", "sentence", "judge"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "You go to the sentencing judge because he retains jurisdiction over that case, during that time that the individual is on a period of probation.", "start": 2213.872, "stop": 2222.961, "duration": 9.09, "cleanText": [["you", "go", "to", "the", "sentencing", "judge", "because", "he", "retain", "jurisdiction", "over", "that", "case", "during", "that", "time", "that", "the", "individual", "be", "on", "a", "period", "of", "probation"]]}, {"text": "Now, I think it's important in this case that the individuals, at this time, are not in confinement.", "start": 2222.961, "stop": 2230.734, "duration": 7.77, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "think", "it", "be", "important", "in", "this", "case", "that", "the", "individual", "at", "this", "time", "be", "not", "in", "confinement"]]}, {"text": "And I was under the misapprehension, and I'll correct that, on page 9 of my brief, and I indicated that confinement resulted... it did not, as Mr. Zell said, initially.", "start": 2230.734, "stop": 2241.539, "duration": 10.81, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "be", "under", "the", "misapprehension", "and", "I", "will", "correct", "that", "on", "page", "of", "my", "brief", "and", "i", "indicate", "that", "confinement", "result", "it", "do", "not", "as", "mr", "zell", "say", "initially"]]}, {"text": "I think the important factor is that these individuals are out on bond, on an appeal bond, that bond was posted on February 13, 1979, which was the date when the judge said that after the hearing in January, of '79, if you don't pay the arrears, I'm going to give you two weeks to pay the arrearage for approximately $1500, then I'm going to revoke probation.", "start": 2241.539, "stop": 2265.307, "duration": 23.77, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "the", "important", "factor", "be", "that", "these", "individual", "be", "out", "on", "bond", "on", "an", "appeal", "bond", "that", "bond", "be", "post", "on", "february", "which", "be", "the", "date", "when", "the", "judge", "say", "that", "after", "the", "hearing", "in", "january", "of", "if", "you", "do", "not", "pay", "the", "arrears", "I", "be", "go", "to", "give", "you", "two", "week", "to", "pay", "the", "arrearage", "for", "approximately", "then", "I", "be", "go", "to", "revoke", "probation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "What was the amount of that bond?", "start": 2265.307, "stop": 2266.74, "duration": 1.43, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "the", "amount", "of", "that", "bond"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Now the bond for Mr. Wood is $20,000, and under the Georgia statutory scheme, the maximum amount... or, the amount that would have to be paid for that bond, according to my figures, would be $1,025.", "start": 2266.74, "stop": 2283.868, "duration": 17.13, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "bond", "for", "mr", "wood", "be", "and", "under", "the", "georgia", "statutory", "scheme", "the", "maximum", "amount", "or", "the", "amount", "that", "would", "have", "to", "be", "pay", "for", "that", "bond", "accord", "to", "my", "figure", "would", "be"]]}, {"text": "The statute is Georgia Code 27-501.", "start": 2283.868, "stop": 2289.505, "duration": 5.64, "cleanText": [["the", "statute", "be", "georgia", "code"]]}, {"text": "That sets out the fact that you can't charge any more than 10 percent of the first five hundred dollars, or any more than five percent on amounts over $500.", "start": 2289.505, "stop": 2299.128, "duration": 9.62, "cleanText": [["that", "set", "out", "the", "fact", "that", "you", "can", "not", "charge", "any", "more", "than", "percent", "of", "the", "first", "five", "hundred", "dollar", "or", "any", "more", "than", "five", "percent", "on", "amount", "over"]]}, {"text": "As to the other two Petitioners, Ms. Allen and Mr. Tante; it was a $10,000 bond and I think my math worked out to something like 525.", "start": 2299.128, "stop": 2311.886, "duration": 12.76, "cleanText": [["as", "to", "the", "other", "two", "petitioner", "ms", "allen", "and", "mr", "tante", "it", "be", "a", "bond", "and", "i", "think", "my", "math", "work", "out", "to", "something", "like"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is there anything in the record to indicate where this indigent got the money to pay that?", "start": 2311.886, "stop": 2319.023, "duration": 7.14, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "anything", "in", "the", "record", "to", "indicate", "where", "this", "indigent", "get", "the", "money", "to", "pay", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, and I think that gets into--", "start": 2319.023, "stop": 2321.158, "duration": 2.13, "cleanText": [["no", "and", "i", "think", "that", "get", "into"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well if it's not in the record, I don't want you to pursue it.", "start": 2321.158, "stop": 2323.192, "duration": 2.03, "cleanText": [["well", "if", "it", "be", "not", "in", "the", "record", "i", "do", "not", "want", "you", "to", "pursue", "it"]]}, {"text": "I just wanted to know if it was in the record.", "start": 2323.192, "stop": 2324.877, "duration": 1.68, "cleanText": [["i", "just", "want", "to", "know", "if", "it", "be", "in", "the", "record"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I think the interesting part of the case, though, which the Court can consider, is in our Appendix A, which is the revocation proceeding in January of 1979, Mr. Zell told the sentencing judge, the trial judge, Judge Alexander that these individuals' previous fines in connection with other cases, had been paid and that he had paid them.", "start": 2324.877, "stop": 2354.646, "duration": 29.77, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "the", "interesting", "part", "of", "the", "case", "though", "which", "the", "court", "can", "consider", "be", "in", "our", "appendix", "a", "which", "be", "the", "revocation", "proceeding", "in", "january", "of", "mr", "zell", "tell", "the", "sentencing", "judge", "the", "trial", "judge", "judge", "alexander", "that", "these", "individual", "previous", "fine", "in", "connection", "with", "other", "case", "have", "be", "pay", "and", "that", "he", "have", "pay", "them"]]}, {"text": "Now,... I think--", "start": 2354.646, "stop": 2355.929, "duration": 1.28, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "think"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "You said previous fines?", "start": 2355.929, "stop": 2357.715, "duration": 1.79, "cleanText": [["you", "say", "previous", "fine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That is correct.", "start": 2357.715, "stop": 2358.998, "duration": 1.28, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "Perhaps I misundertsood Mr. Zell, but I thought that this was their first conviction.", "start": 2358.998, "stop": 2363.269, "duration": 4.27, "cleanText": [["perhaps", "i", "misundertsood", "mr", "zell", "but", "i", "think", "that", "this", "be", "their", "first", "conviction"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "All right.", "start": 2363.269, "stop": 2364.035, "duration": 0.77, "cleanText": [["all", "right"]]}, {"text": "If I can, the scenario is, this is their first conviction.", "start": 2364.035, "stop": 2368.223, "duration": 4.19, "cleanText": [["if", "i", "can", "the", "scenario", "be", "this", "be", "their", "first", "conviction"]]}, {"text": "This is what happened: each one of them was arrested and they pursued their constitutional right to submit the matter before a jury; a jury in March of 1977 found them guilty as charged and the judge at that time said I'm going to put your sentence at 12 months, the maximum for these convictions of distributing obscene materials, since it's considered an aggravating... a misdemeanor of a high and aggravating nature, is 12 months and a $5,000 fine or both.", "start": 2368.223, "stop": 2400.192, "duration": 31.97, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "what", "happen", "each", "one", "of", "them", "be", "arrest", "and", "they", "pursue", "their", "constitutional", "right", "to", "submit", "the", "matter", "before", "a", "jury", "a", "jury", "in", "march", "of", "find", "them", "guilty", "as", "charge", "and", "the", "judge", "at", "that", "time", "say", "I", "be", "go", "to", "put", "your", "sentence", "at", "month", "the", "maximum", "for", "these", "conviction", "of", "distribute", "obscene", "material", "since", "it", "be", "consider", "an", "aggravating", "a", "misdemeanor", "of", "a", "high", "and", "aggravating", "nature", "be", "month", "and", "a", "fine", "or", "both"]]}, {"text": "Now, after that time, they appealed to the Court of Appeals, then to the Supreme Court of Georgia, then a writ of certiorari.", "start": 2400.192, "stop": 2408.531, "duration": 8.34, "cleanText": [["now", "after", "that", "time", "they", "appeal", "to", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "then", "to", "the", "supreme", "court", "of", "georgia", "then", "a", "writ", "of", "certiorari"]]}, {"text": "In the interim, between the time of the October 23, 1978 order when the judge says all right, I'm going to... the terms and conditions of probation start on this date.", "start": 2408.531, "stop": 2420.521, "duration": 11.99, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "interim", "between", "the", "time", "of", "the", "october", "order", "when", "the", "judge", "say", "all", "right", "I", "be", "go", "to", "the", "term", "and", "condition", "of", "probation", "start", "on", "this", "date"]]}, {"text": "They entered pleas of guilty to subsequent offenses.", "start": 2420.521, "stop": 2425.575, "duration": 5.05, "cleanText": [["they", "enter", "plea", "of", "guilty", "to", "subsequent", "offense"]]}, {"text": "It was those subsequent offenses which are referred to in our Appendix A on the brief in opposition to writ of certiorari, where Mr. Zell tells the judge yes, I paid the fine, or the employers gave me the money to pay these fines--", "start": 2425.575, "stop": 2440.835, "duration": 15.26, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "those", "subsequent", "offense", "which", "be", "refer", "to", "in", "our", "appendix", "a", "on", "the", "brief", "in", "opposition", "to", "writ", "of", "certiorari", "where", "mr", "zell", "tell", "the", "judge", "yes", "i", "pay", "the", "fine", "or", "the", "employer", "give", "me", "the", "money", "to", "pay", "these", "fine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well the could the judge have revoked the then pending probation because of that conviction of a subsequent crime?", "start": 2440.835, "stop": 2450.108, "duration": 9.27, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "could", "the", "judge", "have", "revoke", "the", "then", "pending", "probation", "because", "of", "that", "conviction", "of", "a", "subsequent", "crime"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, he could have, I believe... well, I believe he could have.", "start": 2450.108, "stop": 2453.994, "duration": 3.89, "cleanText": [["yes", "he", "could", "have", "i", "believe", "well", "i", "believe", "he", "could", "have"]]}, {"text": "Well, I think the important part is, of the case, is that he had... and what we're talking about here is sentencing discretion of a trial judge.", "start": 2453.994, "stop": 2464.617, "duration": 10.62, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "the", "important", "part", "be", "of", "the", "case", "be", "that", "he", "have", "and", "what", "we", "be", "talk", "about", "here", "be", "sentence", "discretion", "of", "a", "trial", "judge"]]}, {"text": "What may he consider?", "start": 2464.617, "stop": 2466.552, "duration": 1.93, "cleanText": [["what", "may", "he", "consider"]]}, {"text": "Can he consider other things?", "start": 2466.552, "stop": 2468.052, "duration": 1.5, "cleanText": [["can", "he", "consider", "other", "thing"]]}, {"text": "Now, in the United States v. Grayson, this Court said yes, the judge could consider the demeanor of the defendant when he said you know, I find your defense to be highly incredible and you know, basically, I think you're putting the sham on the Court.", "start": 2468.052, "stop": 2485.831, "duration": 17.78, "cleanText": [["now", "in", "the", "united", "state", "v", "grayson", "this", "court", "say", "yes", "the", "judge", "could", "consider", "the", "demeanor", "of", "the", "defendant", "when", "he", "say", "you", "know", "i", "find", "your", "defense", "to", "be", "highly", "incredible", "and", "you", "know", "basically", "i", "think", "you", "be", "put", "the", "sham", "on", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "By analogy, cannot the trial judge consider representations to him by third parties that we will pay the fines?", "start": 2485.831, "stop": 2496.438, "duration": 10.61, "cleanText": [["by", "analogy", "can", "not", "the", "trial", "judge", "consider", "representation", "to", "him", "by", "third", "party", "that", "we", "will", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}, {"text": "Now, what does this do in the mind of the trial judge?", "start": 2496.438, "stop": 2498.94, "duration": 2.5, "cleanText": [["now", "what", "do", "this", "do", "in", "the", "mind", "of", "the", "trial", "judge"]]}, {"text": "He says yes, we're going to put you, I'm going to give you 12 months, and a $5,000 fine.", "start": 2498.94, "stop": 2504.427, "duration": 5.49, "cleanText": [["he", "say", "yes", "we", "be", "go", "to", "put", "you", "I", "be", "go", "to", "give", "you", "month", "and", "a", "fine"]]}, {"text": "Or the 12 months and $5,000 authorized by law.", "start": 2504.427, "stop": 2507.546, "duration": 3.12, "cleanText": [["or", "the", "month", "and", "authorize", "by", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "What does the record show, if anything, about who paid the bond or the fee of $1,000, or more?", "start": 2507.546, "stop": 2515.183, "duration": 7.64, "cleanText": [["what", "do", "the", "record", "show", "if", "anything", "about", "who", "pay", "the", "bond", "or", "the", "fee", "of", "or", "more"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Now, the bond as to--", "start": 2515.183, "stop": 2519.401, "duration": 4.22, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "bond", "as", "to"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "The bond for the... continued liberty, while this case is--", "start": 2519.401, "stop": 2526.305, "duration": 6.9, "cleanText": [["the", "bond", "for", "the", "continue", "liberty", "while", "this", "case", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well I--", "start": 2526.305, "stop": 2526.689, "duration": 0.38, "cleanText": [["well", "i"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Isn't there something in--", "start": 2526.689, "stop": 2528.524, "duration": 1.84, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "there", "something", "in"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Mr. Chief Justice Burger, it was not until the 27th of October that I found out that these individuals had a bond posted.", "start": 2528.524, "stop": 2538.196, "duration": 9.67, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "burger", "it", "be", "not", "until", "the", "th", "of", "october", "that", "i", "find", "out", "that", "these", "individual", "have", "a", "bond", "post"]]}, {"text": "Now perhaps I was negligent in some regard in not checking this out sooner, but in part, I relied in part on the solicitor's office to give me some of the background material that I initially supplied the Court with in our brief... petition for certiorari--", "start": 2538.196, "stop": 2553.558, "duration": 15.36, "cleanText": [["now", "perhaps", "i", "be", "negligent", "in", "some", "regard", "in", "not", "check", "this", "out", "sooner", "but", "in", "part", "i", "rely", "in", "part", "on", "the", "solicitor", "s", "office", "to", "give", "me", "some", "of", "the", "background", "material", "that", "i", "initially", "supply", "the", "court", "with", "in", "our", "brief", "petition", "for", "certiorari"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well wasn't there some statement by counsel at one of these hearings that the employer had paid the bonds--", "start": 2553.558, "stop": 2559.628, "duration": 6.07, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "not", "there", "some", "statement", "by", "counsel", "at", "one", "of", "these", "hearing", "that", "the", "employer", "have", "pay", "the", "bond"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Oh Mr. Chief Justice Burger, yes, that's in regard to... well, two things.", "start": 2559.628, "stop": 2565.366, "duration": 5.74, "cleanText": [["oh", "mr", "chief", "justice", "burger", "yes", "that", "be", "in", "regard", "to", "well", "two", "thing"]]}, {"text": "I believe the Petitioners all said, and this is important, I think, they said that when we were employed, our employers told us that if at any time during our employment you're arrested or anything we will pay your fines, we will make sure that bond is arranged and we will provide you with legal representation.", "start": 2565.366, "stop": 2587.045, "duration": 21.68, "cleanText": [["i", "believe", "the", "petitioner", "all", "say", "and", "this", "be", "important", "i", "think", "they", "say", "that", "when", "we", "we", "be", "employ", "our", "employer", "tell", "us", "that", "if", "at", "any", "time", "during", "our", "employment", "you", "be", "arrest", "or", "anything", "we", "will", "pay", "your", "fine", "we", "will", "make", "sure", "that", "bond", "be", "arrange", "and", "we", "will", "provide", "you", "with", "legal", "representation"]]}, {"text": "Now in the appendix, there is indication that the King Bonding Company paid the bonds for these individuals when they were arrested... and, I would assume, the continuing appeal bonds until October 23rd, 1978.", "start": 2587.045, "stop": 2603.322, "duration": 16.28, "cleanText": [["now", "in", "the", "appendix", "there", "be", "indication", "that", "the", "king", "bond", "company", "pay", "the", "bond", "for", "these", "individual", "when", "they", "we", "be", "arrest", "and", "i", "would", "assume", "the", "continue", "appeal", "bond", "until", "october", "rd"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Mr. Attorney General, if that's true, why wasn't the owner arrested?", "start": 2603.322, "stop": 2607.626, "duration": 4.3, "cleanText": [["mr", "attorney", "general", "if", "that", "be", "true", "why", "be", "not", "the", "owner", "arrest"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Justice Marshall, I have no idea, and I cannot speak for the solicitor of Fulton County.", "start": 2607.626, "stop": 2613.43, "duration": 5.8, "cleanText": [["mr", "justice", "marshall", "i", "have", "no", "idea", "and", "i", "can", "not", "speak", "for", "the", "solicitor", "of", "fulton", "county"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "I understand.", "start": 2613.43, "stop": 2613.863, "duration": 0.43, "cleanText": [["i", "understand"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Now these individuals also indicated... and I think the representation is, too, properly to the Court, that here, the employer has... the employer even told one of them, I believe it was Mr. Tante, there was an indication in the probation revocation hearing, well how did you know to get Mr. Zell?", "start": 2613.863, "stop": 2638.062, "duration": 24.2, "cleanText": [["now", "these", "individual", "also", "indicate", "and", "i", "think", "the", "representation", "be", "too", "properly", "to", "the", "court", "that", "here", "the", "employer", "have", "the", "employer", "even", "tell", "one", "of", "them", "i", "believe", "it", "be", "mr", "tante", "there", "be", "an", "indication", "in", "the", "probation", "revocation", "hearing", "well", "how", "do", "you", "know", "to", "get", "mr", "zell"]]}, {"text": "I believe there is testimony in there that he had represented them previously.", "start": 2638.062, "stop": 2642.216, "duration": 4.15, "cleanText": [["i", "believe", "there", "be", "testimony", "in", "there", "that", "he", "have", "represent", "them", "previously"]]}, {"text": "And I believe there's also testimony in that revocation hearing that the... it had been suggested by the employer to contact Mr. Zell.", "start": 2642.216, "stop": 2651.905, "duration": 9.69, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "believe", "there", "be", "also", "testimony", "in", "that", "revocation", "hearing", "that", "the", "it", "have", "be", "suggest", "by", "the", "employer", "to", "contact", "mr", "zell"]]}, {"text": "And there's also an indication in the record that Mister... an inference, anyway, because I don't think it comes out clearly... an inference that the employer paid Mr. Zell's fee.", "start": 2651.905, "stop": 2663.529, "duration": 11.62, "cleanText": [["and", "there", "be", "also", "an", "indication", "in", "the", "record", "that", "mister", "an", "inference", "anyway", "because", "i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "come", "out", "clearly", "an", "inference", "that", "the", "employer", "pay", "mr", "zell", "s", "fee"]]}, {"text": "Now, I think we need to--", "start": 2663.529, "stop": 2664.729, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "think", "we", "need", "to"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Dunsmore, let me ask you one question about the appendix on page 21, and it's in the last paragraph there where that court states, and this is the trial court, order of probation,", "start": 2664.729, "stop": 2680.491, "duration": 15.76, "cleanText": [["mr", "dunsmore", "let", "me", "ask", "you", "one", "question", "about", "the", "appendix", "on", "page", "and", "it", "be", "in", "the", "last", "paragraph", "there", "where", "that", "court", "state", "and", "this", "be", "the", "trial", "court", "order", "of", "probation"]]}, {"text": "\"It is further ordered that the Court, and the Defendant is hereby advised that the Court may at any time revoke or modify any conditions of this probation or change the period of probation, and may discharge the Defendant from probation. \"", "start": 2680.491, "stop": 2698.719, "duration": 18.23, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "further", "order", "that", "the", "court", "and", "the", "defendant", "be", "hereby", "advise", "that", "the", "court", "may", "at", "any", "time", "revoke", "or", "modify", "any", "condition", "of", "this", "probation", "or", "change", "the", "period", "of", "probation", "and", "may", "discharge", "the", "defendant", "from", "probation"]]}, {"text": "Was any application made in this case to discharge the Defendant from probation?", "start": 2698.719, "stop": 2706.406, "duration": 7.69, "cleanText": [["be", "any", "application", "make", "in", "this", "case", "to", "discharge", "the", "defendant", "from", "probation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--None on the record, now.", "start": 2706.406, "stop": 2708.574, "duration": 2.17, "cleanText": [["none", "on", "the", "record", "now"]]}, {"text": "And I say that with... well for the qualified remark, that on page 71, of the probation revocation hearing, there is an indication from Mr. Zell that I wrote the court.", "start": 2708.574, "stop": 2720.566, "duration": 11.99, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "say", "that", "with", "well", "for", "the", "qualified", "remark", "that", "on", "page", "of", "the", "probation", "revocation", "hearing", "there", "be", "an", "indication", "from", "mr", "zell", "that", "i", "write", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "But I think as we pointed out in our brief in this case, at the time the sentences were imposed, the Defendants... Petitioners in this case... sat back in silence.", "start": 2720.566, "stop": 2731.957, "duration": 11.39, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "think", "as", "we", "point", "out", "in", "our", "brief", "in", "this", "case", "at", "the", "time", "the", "sentence", "we", "be", "impose", "the", "defendant", "petitioner", "in", "this", "case", "sit", "back", "in", "silence"]]}, {"text": "They never went in to the probation officers at that time and said, you know, we can't pay.", "start": 2731.957, "stop": 2737.844, "duration": 5.89, "cleanText": [["they", "never", "go", "in", "to", "the", "probation", "officer", "at", "that", "time", "and", "say", "you", "know", "we", "can", "not", "pay"]]}, {"text": "There's an indication that the probation officer said we'll accept partial payments, and they never went in and told the... indicated to their probation supervisors that you know, we could pay a lesser amount.", "start": 2737.844, "stop": 2751.035, "duration": 13.19, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "an", "indication", "that", "the", "probation", "officer", "say", "we", "will", "accept", "partial", "payment", "and", "they", "never", "go", "in", "and", "tell", "the", "indicate", "to", "their", "probation", "supervisor", "that", "you", "know", "we", "could", "pay", "a", "less", "amount"]]}, {"text": "They refused, and I use the word refused, to pay the fine because they were under the impression, and I think rightly so, from... on the conditions of employment... that their employers would pay the fine.", "start": 2751.035, "stop": 2764.328, "duration": 13.29, "cleanText": [["they", "refuse", "and", "i", "use", "the", "word", "refuse", "to", "pay", "the", "fine", "because", "they", "we", "be", "under", "the", "impression", "and", "i", "think", "rightly", "so", "from", "on", "the", "condition", "of", "employment", "that", "their", "employer", "would", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}, {"text": "And therefore they took no action.", "start": 2764.328, "stop": 2766.797, "duration": 2.47, "cleanText": [["and", "therefore", "they", "take", "no", "action"]]}, {"text": "Now, I think what that amounts to in this case, regardless of funds, is are we not deceiving a trial judge?", "start": 2766.797, "stop": 2774.701, "duration": 7.9, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "think", "what", "that", "amount", "to", "in", "this", "case", "regardless", "of", "fund", "be", "be", "we", "not", "deceive", "a", "trial", "judge"]]}, {"text": "And as Mr. Justice Marshall says, let the judge go down the road,... you know, many times you say well can silence be a condoning aspect?", "start": 2774.701, "stop": 2784.391, "duration": 9.69, "cleanText": [["and", "as", "mr", "justice", "marshall", "say", "let", "the", "judge", "go", "down", "the", "road", "you", "know", "many", "time", "you", "say", "well", "can", "silence", "be", "a", "condone", "aspect"]]}, {"text": "I think it can, in this situation.", "start": 2784.391, "stop": 2787.176, "duration": 2.78, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "can", "in", "this", "situation"]]}, {"text": "I think we're talking about the integrity of the sentencing function of the criminal justice system.", "start": 2787.176, "stop": 2794.53, "duration": 7.35, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "we", "be", "talk", "about", "the", "integrity", "of", "the", "sentence", "function", "of", "the", "criminal", "justice", "system"]]}, {"text": "To allow criminal defendants to mislead a judge or, that is, to not bring to his attention facts that are different, let the judge rely on it, get the benefit of a lesser sentence, and then come back in and say, gee I'm sorry, we just didn't have any money.", "start": 2794.53, "stop": 2812.409, "duration": 17.88, "cleanText": [["to", "allow", "criminal", "defendant", "to", "mislead", "a", "judge", "or", "that", "be", "to", "not", "bring", "to", "his", "attention", "fact", "that", "be", "different", "let", "the", "judge", "rely", "on", "it", "get", "the", "benefit", "of", "a", "less", "sentence", "and", "then", "come", "back", "in", "and", "say", "gee", "I", "be", "sorry", "we", "just", "do", "not", "have", "any", "money"]]}, {"text": "Particularly when you had one year and seven months... 19 months intervening from March of 1977 to October of 1978 when they were actually put under probation supervisors.", "start": 2812.409, "stop": 2826.818, "duration": 14.41, "cleanText": [["particularly", "when", "you", "have", "one", "year", "and", "seven", "month", "month", "intervene", "from", "march", "of", "to", "october", "of", "when", "they", "we", "be", "actually", "put", "under", "probation", "supervisor"]]}, {"text": "In that period of time they had an opportunity to check with their employer, and say, are you going to pay the fine, the record is silent, they did nothing.", "start": 2826.818, "stop": 2834.841, "duration": 8.02, "cleanText": [["in", "that", "period", "of", "time", "they", "have", "an", "opportunity", "to", "check", "with", "their", "employer", "and", "say", "be", "you", "go", "to", "pay", "the", "fine", "the", "record", "be", "silent", "they", "do", "nothing"]]}, {"text": "They never, at any time, went and tried to pay the fine.", "start": 2834.841, "stop": 2839.676, "duration": 4.84, "cleanText": [["they", "never", "at", "any", "time", "go", "and", "try", "to", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}, {"text": "There's no showing that they went out to see if they could borrow any money, to my understanding.", "start": 2839.676, "stop": 2844.48, "duration": 4.8, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "show", "that", "they", "go", "out", "to", "see", "if", "they", "could", "borrow", "any", "money", "to", "my", "understanding"]]}, {"text": "All of them were earning some sort of money and and the word indigent, I think, has been used loosely in this case.", "start": 2844.48, "stop": 2853.236, "duration": 8.76, "cleanText": [["all", "of", "them", "we", "be", "earn", "some", "sort", "of", "money", "and", "and", "the", "word", "indigent", "i", "think", "have", "be", "use", "loosely", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "One individual making $525 a month, another one $400 to $500 a month, and the one lady was on unemployment.", "start": 2853.236, "stop": 2861.808, "duration": 8.57, "cleanText": [["one", "individual", "make", "a", "month", "another", "one", "to", "a", "month", "and", "the", "one", "lady", "be", "on", "unemployment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Did they ever ask the Court to reduce the amount of the installments and put them over a longer period of time?", "start": 2861.808, "stop": 2867.628, "duration": 5.82, "cleanText": [["do", "they", "ever", "ask", "the", "court", "to", "reduce", "the", "amount", "of", "the", "installment", "and", "put", "them", "over", "a", "long", "period", "of", "time"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, there was no effort made at any time to reduce the installments or to seek anything else.", "start": 2867.628, "stop": 2874.982, "duration": 7.35, "cleanText": [["no", "there", "be", "no", "effort", "make", "at", "any", "time", "to", "reduce", "the", "installment", "or", "to", "seek", "anything", "else"]]}, {"text": "As a matter of fact, on page 69 of the Appendix... Appendix A, which is not the brown appendix, but the one appended to our brief in opposition... the judge, Judge Alexander, says I didn't ask the question because I thought I could enforce the agreement.", "start": 2874.982, "stop": 2894.546, "duration": 19.56, "cleanText": [["as", "a", "matter", "of", "fact", "on", "page", "of", "the", "appendix", "appendix", "a", "which", "be", "not", "the", "brown", "appendix", "but", "the", "one", "append", "to", "our", "brief", "in", "opposition", "the", "judge", "judge", "alexander", "say", "i", "do", "not", "ask", "the", "question", "because", "i", "think", "i", "could", "enforce", "the", "agreement"]]}, {"text": "Right there, there's evidence right there that the judge was under the impression that the third parties would pay this fine.", "start": 2894.546, "stop": 2903.101, "duration": 8.56, "cleanText": [["right", "there", "there", "be", "evidence", "right", "there", "that", "the", "judge", "be", "under", "the", "impression", "that", "the", "third", "party", "would", "pay", "this", "fine"]]}, {"text": "Now why should the judge be able to look to third parties?", "start": 2903.101, "stop": 2906.803, "duration": 3.7, "cleanText": [["now", "why", "should", "the", "judge", "be", "able", "to", "look", "to", "third", "party"]]}, {"text": "In the probation context, just as if we're putting the individual out on parole, we're trying to find an alternative to confinement.", "start": 2906.803, "stop": 2915.793, "duration": 8.99, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "probation", "context", "just", "as", "if", "we", "be", "put", "the", "individual", "out", "on", "parole", "we", "be", "try", "to", "find", "an", "alternative", "to", "confinement"]]}, {"text": "Now an alternative to confinement has the purpose of rehabilitation.", "start": 2915.793, "stop": 2922.632, "duration": 6.84, "cleanText": [["now", "an", "alternative", "to", "confinement", "have", "the", "purpose", "of", "rehabilitation"]]}, {"text": "We want to deminimize the amount of supervision that the Court has to engage in.", "start": 2922.632, "stop": 2927.901, "duration": 5.27, "cleanText": [["we", "want", "to", "deminimize", "the", "amount", "of", "supervision", "that", "the", "court", "have", "to", "engage", "in"]]}, {"text": "Now if the Court can look to a citizen, an employer or somebody in the community, that aids the Court in its carrying out of its rehabilitative function.", "start": 2927.901, "stop": 2941.311, "duration": 13.41, "cleanText": [["now", "if", "the", "court", "can", "look", "to", "a", "citizen", "an", "employer", "or", "somebody", "in", "the", "community", "that", "aid", "the", "court", "in", "its", "carry", "out", "of", "its", "rehabilitative", "function"]]}, {"text": "Particularly, you know, in the context when we put a man on parole; one of the things parole boards generally ask... where are you going in the community, who will vouch for you, do you have a job, is there somebody in the community grassroots that we can look to to assist us in rehabilitating you?", "start": 2941.311, "stop": 2961.69, "duration": 20.38, "cleanText": [["particularly", "you", "know", "in", "the", "context", "when", "we", "put", "a", "man", "on", "parole", "one", "of", "the", "thing", "parole", "board", "generally", "ask", "where", "be", "you", "go", "in", "the", "community", "who", "will", "vouch", "for", "you", "do", "you", "have", "a", "job", "be", "there", "somebody", "in", "the", "community", "grassroots", "that", "we", "can", "look", "to", "to", "assist", "us", "in", "rehabilitate", "you"]]}, {"text": "Now that same factor must be viewed in the eyes of the sentencing judge.", "start": 2961.69, "stop": 2965.059, "duration": 3.37, "cleanText": [["now", "that", "same", "factor", "must", "be", "view", "in", "the", "eye", "of", "the", "sentence", "judge"]]}, {"text": "Now, Mr. Zell and Petitioners say well gee, that was an illegal agreement.", "start": 2965.059, "stop": 2970.38, "duration": 5.32, "cleanText": [["now", "mr", "zell", "and", "petitioner", "say", "well", "gee", "that", "be", "an", "illegal", "agreement"]]}, {"text": "That is, illegal to the extent that you pre suppose that the individual was hired with the purpose of violating the law.", "start": 2970.38, "stop": 2979.569, "duration": 9.19, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "illegal", "to", "the", "extent", "that", "you", "pre", "suppose", "that", "the", "individual", "be", "hire", "with", "the", "purpose", "of", "violate", "the", "law"]]}, {"text": "But I think the judge rationally could look to the employers because if they put a stake up in the community for an employer, there's going to be continued employment.", "start": 2979.569, "stop": 2988.841, "duration": 9.27, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "think", "the", "judge", "rationally", "could", "look", "to", "the", "employer", "because", "if", "they", "put", "a", "stake", "up", "in", "the", "community", "for", "an", "employer", "there", "be", "go", "to", "be", "continue", "employment"]]}, {"text": "Now one of the terms of the probation was that they continue on employment.", "start": 2988.841, "stop": 2993.395, "duration": 4.55, "cleanText": [["now", "one", "of", "the", "term", "of", "the", "probation", "be", "that", "they", "continue", "on", "employment"]]}, {"text": "If that individual is working he can contribute to his family.", "start": 2993.395, "stop": 2998.113, "duration": 4.72, "cleanText": [["if", "that", "individual", "be", "work", "he", "can", "contribute", "to", "his", "family"]]}, {"text": "He doesn't become a burden to society.", "start": 2998.113, "stop": 3000.915, "duration": 2.8, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "not", "become", "a", "burden", "to", "society"]]}, {"text": "The collection of fine in this case is not like Tate v. Short, where they said it's a revenue measure.", "start": 3000.915, "stop": 3005.969, "duration": 5.05, "cleanText": [["the", "collection", "of", "fine", "in", "this", "case", "be", "not", "like", "tate", "v", "short", "where", "they", "say", "it", "be", "a", "revenue", "measure"]]}, {"text": "The judge in this case is looking to third parties because they are going to help in the rehabilitative aspect of that individual.", "start": 3005.969, "stop": 3012.057, "duration": 6.09, "cleanText": [["the", "judge", "in", "this", "case", "be", "look", "to", "third", "party", "because", "they", "be", "go", "to", "help", "in", "the", "rehabilitative", "aspect", "of", "that", "individual"]]}, {"text": "And also--", "start": 3012.057, "stop": 3012.89, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["and", "also"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Isn't the judge a part of the whole thing?", "start": 3012.89, "stop": 3016.092, "duration": 3.2, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "the", "judge", "a", "part", "of", "the", "whole", "thing"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--A party?", "start": 3016.092, "stop": 3017.011, "duration": 0.92, "cleanText": [["a", "party"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "How can a judge take the word of a man who is the criminal?", "start": 3017.011, "stop": 3023.08, "duration": 6.07, "cleanText": [["how", "can", "a", "judge", "take", "the", "word", "of", "a", "man", "who", "be", "the", "criminal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think it's... in any case--", "start": 3023.08, "stop": 3026.782, "duration": 3.7, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "it", "be", "in", "any", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "And the only thing that the owner is doing is paying additional taxes.", "start": 3026.782, "stop": 3031.936, "duration": 5.15, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "only", "thing", "that", "the", "owner", "be", "do", "be", "pay", "additional", "tax"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I don't consider it paying additional taxes, and I think--", "start": 3031.936, "stop": 3034.603, "duration": 2.67, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "consider", "it", "pay", "additional", "tax", "and", "i", "think"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "If the agreement is understood between the prosecution, the defense and the judge, that the guilty party will pay the fine of the guys that are convicted.", "start": 3034.603, "stop": 3050.498, "duration": 15.89, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "agreement", "be", "understood", "between", "the", "prosecution", "the", "defense", "and", "the", "judge", "that", "the", "guilty", "party", "will", "pay", "the", "fine", "of", "the", "guy", "that", "be", "convict"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well I think we're going one--", "start": 3050.498, "stop": 3051.548, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "we", "be", "go", "one"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is that all, that's understood?", "start": 3051.548, "stop": 3054.334, "duration": 2.79, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "all", "that", "be", "understand"]]}, {"text": "Do you have any problems with that?", "start": 3054.334, "stop": 3056.819, "duration": 2.49, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "have", "any", "problem", "with", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well let me explain that, Mr. Justice Marshall.", "start": 3056.819, "stop": 3060.621, "duration": 3.8, "cleanText": [["well", "let", "me", "explain", "that", "mr", "justice", "marshall"]]}, {"text": "I think we're reading too much into it and we're... we're reading too much into it, because that assumes that the solicitor knew that the employer was going to pay the fine.", "start": 3060.621, "stop": 3073.097, "duration": 12.48, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "we", "be", "read", "too", "much", "into", "it", "and", "we", "be", "we", "be", "read", "too", "much", "into", "it", "because", "that", "assume", "that", "the", "solicitor", "know", "that", "the", "employer", "be", "go", "to", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "I thought you said that that was stated in open court.", "start": 3073.097, "stop": 3076.399, "duration": 3.3, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "you", "say", "that", "that", "be", "state", "in", "open", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't believe that the solicitor stated it in open court.", "start": 3076.399, "stop": 3078.582, "duration": 2.18, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "believe", "that", "the", "solicitor", "state", "it", "in", "open", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "I didn't say the solicitor, I said somebody did.", "start": 3078.582, "stop": 3081.817, "duration": 3.24, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "say", "the", "solicitor", "i", "say", "somebody", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right, and that was the Petitioners--", "start": 3081.817, "stop": 3082.969, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["right", "and", "that", "be", "the", "petitioner"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "And the solicitor--", "start": 3082.969, "stop": 3083.553, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "solicitor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--in this case.", "start": 3083.553, "stop": 3084.103, "duration": 0.55, "cleanText": [["in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "--was there, wasn't he?", "start": 3084.103, "stop": 3084.905, "duration": 0.8, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "be", "not", "he"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 3084.905, "stop": 3085.555, "duration": 0.65, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "So he heard it, didn't he?", "start": 3085.555, "stop": 3087.255, "duration": 1.7, "cleanText": [["so", "he", "hear", "it", "do", "not", "he"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 3087.255, "stop": 3088.357, "duration": 1.1, "cleanText": [["right"]]}, {"text": "But I think the key, Mr. Justice Marshall and the Court, is that when an employer in this situation says that he will vouch for this individual... particularly rehabilitative efforts... is he not telling the Court that he is going to see to it that his conduct conforms to the law?", "start": 3088.357, "stop": 3106.001, "duration": 17.64, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "think", "the", "key", "mr", "justice", "marshall", "and", "the", "court", "be", "that", "when", "an", "employer", "in", "this", "situation", "say", "that", "he", "will", "vouch", "for", "this", "individual", "particularly", "rehabilitative", "effort", "be", "he", "not", "tell", "the", "court", "that", "he", "be", "go", "to", "see", "to", "it", "that", "his", "conduct", "conforms", "to", "the", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would it be the same as a dote?", "start": 3106.001, "stop": 3110.37, "duration": 4.37, "cleanText": [["would", "it", "be", "the", "same", "as", "a", "dote"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would it be the same as--", "start": 3110.37, "stop": 3111.253, "duration": 0.88, "cleanText": [["would", "it", "be", "the", "same", "as"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "That the King tendered a dote says to the Court that I'll pay the fine for these guys?", "start": 3111.253, "stop": 3117.376, "duration": 6.12, "cleanText": [["that", "the", "king", "tender", "a", "dote", "say", "to", "the", "court", "that", "I", "will", "pay", "the", "fine", "for", "these", "guy"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I think you could say--", "start": 3117.376, "stop": 3117.992, "duration": 0.62, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "you", "could", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would that be all right?", "start": 3117.992, "stop": 3118.776, "duration": 0.78, "cleanText": [["would", "that", "be", "all", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I think you could say, because--", "start": 3118.776, "stop": 3119.842, "duration": 1.07, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "you", "could", "say", "because"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would that be all right?", "start": 3119.842, "stop": 3121.178, "duration": 1.34, "cleanText": [["would", "that", "be", "all", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Isn't that an indication that he's got a stake in this individual and that he's going to conform his conduct to the law?", "start": 3121.178, "stop": 3127.498, "duration": 6.32, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "that", "an", "indication", "that", "he", "be", "get", "a", "stake", "in", "this", "individual", "and", "that", "he", "be", "go", "to", "conform", "his", "conduct", "to", "the", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thurgood Marshall", "textObjs": [{"text": "And you think the Court would go along with that?", "start": 3127.498, "stop": 3129.032, "duration": 1.53, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "think", "the", "court", "would", "go", "along", "with", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well I don't know, but I think it's a reasonable basis, a rational basis for the Court to consider; that if somebody's going to pay some money out for them, are they going to continue to hire this individual and why would they pay the fines if they thought that the conduct... to continue, would they continue to violate the law?", "start": 3129.032, "stop": 3146.36, "duration": 17.33, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "do", "not", "know", "but", "i", "think", "it", "be", "a", "reasonable", "basis", "a", "rational", "basis", "for", "the", "court", "to", "consider", "that", "if", "somebody", "s", "go", "to", "pay", "some", "money", "out", "for", "them", "be", "they", "go", "to", "continue", "to", "hire", "this", "individual", "and", "why", "would", "they", "pay", "the", "fine", "if", "they", "think", "that", "the", "conduct", "to", "continue", "would", "they", "continue", "to", "violate", "the", "law"]]}, {"text": "You know, Mr. Zell says that to continue to work there would mean that they would violate the terms of their probation; that assumes that the conduct that the employer in this case has vouched for is going to continue.", "start": 3146.36, "stop": 3158.117, "duration": 11.76, "cleanText": [["you", "know", "mr", "zell", "say", "that", "to", "continue", "to", "work", "there", "would", "mean", "that", "they", "would", "violate", "the", "term", "of", "their", "probation", "that", "assume", "that", "the", "conduct", "that", "the", "employer", "in", "this", "case", "have", "vouch", "for", "be", "go", "to", "continue"]]}, {"text": "And I don't think you can make that assumption.", "start": 3158.117, "stop": 3160.686, "duration": 2.57, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "do", "not", "think", "you", "can", "make", "that", "assumption"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Dunsmore, I'm not sure I understood why you think all of this is relevant.", "start": 3160.686, "stop": 3166.207, "duration": 5.52, "cleanText": [["mr", "dunsmore", "I", "be", "not", "sure", "i", "understood", "why", "you", "think", "all", "of", "this", "be", "relevant"]]}, {"text": "As the case comes to us, it's been determined by your Court of Appeals that it was established at the revocation hearing that these defendants were not able to pay these fines.", "start": 3166.207, "stop": 3178.465, "duration": 12.26, "cleanText": [["as", "the", "case", "come", "to", "us", "it", "be", "be", "determine", "by", "your", "court", "of", "appeal", "that", "it", "be", "establish", "at", "the", "revocation", "hearing", "that", "these", "defendant", "we", "be", "not", "able", "to", "pay", "these", "fine"]]}, {"text": "That's what the... that's what the Court of Appeals said, it said at the revocation hearings it was established that none of the Appellants had the financial resources to make the payments.", "start": 3178.465, "stop": 3188.222, "duration": 9.76, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "what", "the", "that", "be", "what", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "say", "it", "say", "at", "the", "revocation", "hearing", "it", "be", "establish", "that", "none", "of", "the", "appellant", "have", "the", "financial", "resource", "to", "make", "the", "payment"]]}, {"text": "And the Court held, nevertheless, that that makes no difference, that you may incarcerate these defendants for failure to pay for the balance of their sentences, in one case the remainder of a two year sentence.", "start": 3188.222, "stop": 3208.467, "duration": 20.24, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "court", "hold", "nevertheless", "that", "that", "make", "no", "difference", "that", "you", "may", "incarcerate", "these", "defendant", "for", "failure", "to", "pay", "for", "the", "balance", "of", "their", "sentence", "in", "one", "case", "the", "remainder", "of", "a", "two", "year", "sentence"]]}, {"text": "Now, isn't that the issue as it comes here?", "start": 3208.467, "stop": 3212.088, "duration": 3.62, "cleanText": [["now", "be", "not", "that", "the", "issue", "as", "it", "come", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct and the Court of Appeals just said--", "start": 3212.088, "stop": 3214.488, "duration": 2.4, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "and", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "just", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well what difference does it make about third parties, or what the agreement was or what the anticipation of the judge was?", "start": 3214.488, "stop": 3221.027, "duration": 6.54, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "difference", "do", "it", "make", "about", "third", "party", "or", "what", "the", "agreement", "be", "or", "what", "the", "anticipation", "of", "the", "judge", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well because--", "start": 3221.027, "stop": 3222.677, "duration": 1.65, "cleanText": [["well", "because"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because the Court of Appeals took it on the assumption it could not... that it had been determined that they were financially unable to pay.", "start": 3222.677, "stop": 3230.133, "duration": 7.46, "cleanText": [["because", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "take", "it", "on", "the", "assumption", "it", "could", "not", "that", "it", "have", "be", "determine", "that", "they", "we", "be", "financially", "unable", "to", "pay"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well the Court of Appeals--", "start": 3230.133, "stop": 3231.583, "duration": 1.45, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "court", "of", "appeal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why don't you just defend that... which you do, I'm sure, you defend that... that even if they couldn't pay, and were unable to pay, it was quite constitutional to put them in jail?", "start": 3231.583, "stop": 3242.54, "duration": 10.96, "cleanText": [["why", "do", "not", "you", "just", "defend", "that", "which", "you", "do", "I", "be", "sure", "you", "defend", "that", "that", "even", "if", "they", "could", "not", "pay", "and", "we", "be", "unable", "to", "pay", "it", "be", "quite", "constitutional", "to", "put", "them", "in", "jail"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Right.", "start": 3242.54, "stop": 3243.256, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["right"]]}, {"text": "And--", "start": 3243.256, "stop": 3243.69, "duration": 0.43, "cleanText": [["and"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Isn't that your position?", "start": 3243.69, "stop": 3244.725, "duration": 1.03, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "that", "your", "position"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That's correct.", "start": 3244.725, "stop": 3245.242, "duration": 0.52, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "And one of the things, we're not... there's no vindictiveness, we're not increasing the sentence at all.", "start": 3245.242, "stop": 3250.979, "duration": 5.74, "cleanText": [["and", "one", "of", "the", "thing", "we", "be", "not", "there", "be", "no", "vindictiveness", "we", "be", "not", "increase", "the", "sentence", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "The sentence was--", "start": 3250.979, "stop": 3251.979, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["the", "sentence", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I--", "start": 3251.979, "stop": 3253.312, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["no", "i"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--you know, 12 months, $5000 fine.", "start": 3253.312, "stop": 3256.7, "duration": 3.39, "cleanText": [["you", "know", "month", "fine"]]}, {"text": "He could, and as Mr. Justice Rehnquist said and you said earlier, he could have slap, right off the board, said, you know, in you go and $5,000 fine.", "start": 3256.7, "stop": 3264.937, "duration": 8.24, "cleanText": [["he", "could", "and", "as", "mr", "justice", "rehnquist", "say", "and", "you", "say", "earlier", "he", "could", "have", "slap", "right", "off", "the", "board", "say", "you", "know", "in", "you", "go", "and", "fine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "--And what if the sentencing judge had known at the time he imposed the... as a condition of probation... that the convicted defendants repay $500 a month, what if he'd known at that very moment that there was no possibility at all that the defendants could repay?", "start": 3264.937, "stop": 3283.867, "duration": 18.93, "cleanText": [["and", "what", "if", "the", "sentencing", "judge", "have", "know", "at", "the", "time", "he", "impose", "the", "as", "a", "condition", "of", "probation", "that", "the", "convict", "defendant", "repay", "a", "month", "what", "if", "he", "have", "know", "at", "that", "very", "moment", "that", "there", "be", "no", "possibility", "at", "all", "that", "the", "defendant", "could", "repay"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well that question is--", "start": 3283.867, "stop": 3285.017, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "question", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Isn't that just the equivalent--", "start": 3285.017, "stop": 3286.385, "duration": 1.37, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "that", "just", "the", "equivalent"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--a little more, that's a little more difficult to add, and I think that assumes... and would put us in a more difficult position, because there, there's an indication of vindictiveness.", "start": 3286.385, "stop": 3297.441, "duration": 11.06, "cleanText": [["a", "little", "more", "that", "be", "a", "little", "more", "difficult", "to", "add", "and", "i", "think", "that", "assumes", "and", "would", "put", "us", "in", "a", "more", "difficult", "position", "because", "there", "there", "be", "an", "indication", "of", "vindictiveness"]]}, {"text": "And as Mr. Zell said, an illusory.", "start": 3297.441, "stop": 3298.893, "duration": 1.45, "cleanText": [["and", "as", "mr", "zell", "say", "an", "illusory"]]}, {"text": "But there's no evidence of any vindictiveness at all in this case.", "start": 3298.893, "stop": 3302.762, "duration": 3.87, "cleanText": [["but", "there", "be", "no", "evidence", "of", "any", "vindictiveness", "at", "all", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "I think that is an essential matter.", "start": 3302.762, "stop": 3305.178, "duration": 2.42, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "be", "an", "essential", "matter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "--What if he had been morally certain that the defendants couldn't meet one or more of the other conditions of probation?", "start": 3305.178, "stop": 3312.634, "duration": 7.46, "cleanText": [["what", "if", "he", "have", "be", "morally", "certain", "that", "the", "defendant", "could", "not", "meet", "one", "or", "more", "of", "the", "other", "condition", "of", "probation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well I agree, I think it makes it far more difficult, because they are... impuning bad faith to the judge and I don't think, on the record here, there's anything to impune lack of judicial integrity on the part of the sentencing judge.", "start": 3312.634, "stop": 3326.377, "duration": 13.74, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "agree", "i", "think", "it", "make", "it", "far", "more", "difficult", "because", "they", "be", "impuning", "bad", "faith", "to", "the", "judge", "and", "i", "do", "not", "think", "on", "the", "record", "here", "there", "be", "anything", "to", "impune", "lack", "of", "judicial", "integrity", "on", "the", "part", "of", "the", "sentence", "judge"]]}, {"text": "I don't think we can go that far, to say that.", "start": 3326.377, "stop": 3329.662, "duration": 3.28, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "we", "can", "go", "that", "far", "to", "say", "that"]]}, {"text": "And then we're hypothesizing and going to all sorts of realms that are not in the confines of this case.", "start": 3329.662, "stop": 3337.816, "duration": 8.15, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "we", "be", "hypothesize", "and", "go", "to", "all", "sort", "of", "realm", "that", "be", "not", "in", "the", "confines", "of", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Attorney General Dunsmore, I got the impression from your adversary that the problem presented by this case is somewhat unique to Georgia.", "start": 3337.816, "stop": 3348.741, "duration": 10.93, "cleanText": [["mr", "attorney", "general", "dunsmore", "i", "get", "the", "impression", "from", "your", "adversary", "that", "the", "problem", "present", "by", "this", "case", "be", "somewhat", "unique", "to", "georgia"]]}, {"text": "Do you have that same impression?", "start": 3348.741, "stop": 3350.076, "duration": 1.34, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "have", "that", "same", "impression"]]}, {"text": "And if so,--", "start": 3350.076, "stop": 3350.409, "duration": 0.33, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "so"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well I'm not too sure of... when he said unique to Georgia... I take it, in terms of the fact that judges don't place individuals on, let's say, spend five nights in the county jail or work for a health facility.", "start": 3350.409, "stop": 3366.685, "duration": 16.28, "cleanText": [["well", "I", "be", "not", "too", "sure", "of", "when", "he", "say", "unique", "to", "georgia", "i", "take", "it", "in", "term", "of", "the", "fact", "that", "judge", "do", "not", "place", "individual", "on", "let", "us", "say", "spend", "five", "night", "in", "the", "county", "jail", "or", "work", "for", "a", "health", "facility"]]}, {"text": "I don't think that's unique, because I have... and this is outside the record, I have heard from other individuals that... where individuals haven't had the fine, that you know, they said, well... like for example, in a traffic case, spend one weekend a month driving around with the hospital ambulance authority or something like that.", "start": 3366.685, "stop": 3384.747, "duration": 18.06, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "that", "be", "unique", "because", "i", "have", "and", "this", "be", "outside", "the", "record", "i", "have", "hear", "from", "other", "individual", "that", "where", "individual", "have", "not", "have", "the", "fine", "that", "you", "know", "they", "say", "well", "like", "for", "example", "in", "a", "traffic", "case", "spend", "one", "weekend", "a", "month", "drive", "around", "with", "the", "hospital", "ambulance", "authority", "or", "something", "like", "that"]]}, {"text": "So, I don't think it's unique to--", "start": 3384.747, "stop": 3388.701, "duration": 3.95, "cleanText": [["so", "i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "be", "unique", "to"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "--But his suggestion seems supported by the fact we've had two previous cases from Georgia where parole was revoked because of inability to pay a fine.", "start": 3388.701, "stop": 3396.205, "duration": 7.5, "cleanText": [["but", "his", "suggestion", "seem", "support", "by", "the", "fact", "we", "have", "have", "two", "previous", "case", "from", "georgia", "where", "parole", "be", "revoke", "because", "of", "inability", "to", "pay", "a", "fine"]]}, {"text": "I just don't know whether it arises in other jurisdictions or not the same way.", "start": 3396.205, "stop": 3401.609, "duration": 5.4, "cleanText": [["i", "just", "do", "not", "know", "whether", "it", "arise", "in", "other", "jurisdiction", "or", "not", "the", "same", "way"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John W. Dunsmore, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Mr. Justice Stevens, I couldn't... couldn't tell you that.", "start": 3401.609, "stop": 3404.494, "duration": 2.89, "cleanText": [["mr", "justice", "stevens", "i", "could", "not", "could", "not", "tell", "you", "that"]]}, {"text": "But I don't think that it... you know, that it's unique, because I do know from some limited experience outside, that you know, other alternatives, depending on who the judge is.", "start": 3404.494, "stop": 3416.135, "duration": 11.64, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "do", "not", "think", "that", "it", "you", "know", "that", "it", "be", "unique", "because", "i", "do", "know", "from", "some", "limited", "experience", "outside", "that", "you", "know", "other", "alternative", "depend", "on", "who", "the", "judge", "be"]]}, {"text": "But what we're getting back to, or what I believe we need to get back to is, the sentencing discretion of the judge and the fact that other alternatives are available or he could consider other alternatives, is it unconstitutional to consider financial resources, and is it unconstitutional to enforce the terms of the sentence which is prescribed by law?", "start": 3416.135, "stop": 3438.132, "duration": 22, "cleanText": [["but", "what", "we", "be", "get", "back", "to", "or", "what", "i", "believe", "we", "need", "to", "get", "back", "to", "be", "the", "sentence", "discretion", "of", "the", "judge", "and", "the", "fact", "that", "other", "alternative", "be", "available", "or", "he", "could", "consider", "other", "alternative", "be", "it", "unconstitutional", "to", "consider", "financial", "resource", "and", "be", "it", "unconstitutional", "to", "enforce", "the", "term", "of", "the", "sentence", "which", "be", "prescribe", "by", "law"]]}, {"text": "And that's exactly what we're faced with, and we say it's not.", "start": 3438.132, "stop": 3442.367, "duration": 4.24, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "exactly", "what", "we", "be", "face", "with", "and", "we", "say", "it", "be", "not"]]}, {"text": "And we say, particularly, that it's not, because there is some element of deception in this case.", "start": 3442.367, "stop": 3450.79, "duration": 8.42, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "say", "particularly", "that", "it", "be", "not", "because", "there", "be", "some", "element", "of", "deception", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "It was, Mr. Justice Marshall said, you know, leading the judge down the path.", "start": 3450.79, "stop": 3454.858, "duration": 4.07, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "mr", "justice", "marshall", "say", "you", "know", "lead", "the", "judge", "down", "the", "path"]]}, {"text": "I, as attorney, and even as a citizen, would find that somewhat disturbing and irreprehensible that somebody sits down and misinterprets or misleads the Court, particularly in the context that we're brought up... particularly the aura of the Court.", "start": 3454.858, "stop": 3475.755, "duration": 20.9, "cleanText": [["i", "as", "attorney", "and", "even", "as", "a", "citizen", "would", "find", "that", "somewhat", "disturb", "and", "irreprehensible", "that", "somebody", "sit", "down", "and", "misinterprets", "or", "mislead", "the", "court", "particularly", "in", "the", "context", "that", "we", "be", "bring", "up", "particularly", "the", "aura", "of", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "--I think most criminal defendants and most individuals, when they are faced in a court situation, tend to be honest.", "start": 3475.755, "stop": 3483.244, "duration": 7.49, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "most", "criminal", "defendant", "and", "most", "individual", "when", "they", "be", "face", "in", "a", "court", "situation", "tend", "to", "be", "honest"]]}, {"text": "Now, and I'm not supposing this case that the defendants were, you know, were less than honest, but they didn't need to speak up and say the third party is paying the fine.", "start": 3483.244, "stop": 3495.652, "duration": 12.41, "cleanText": [["now", "and", "I", "be", "not", "suppose", "this", "case", "that", "the", "defendant", "we", "be", "you", "know", "we", "be", "less", "than", "honest", "but", "they", "do", "not", "need", "to", "speak", "up", "and", "say", "the", "third", "party", "be", "pay", "the", "fine"]]}, {"text": "I said that after 19 months, particularly on October 23, 1978, or even during that period of time, why didn't they go to their attorney and say look, there's just no way we can pay it.", "start": 3495.652, "stop": 3508.126, "duration": 12.47, "cleanText": [["i", "say", "that", "after", "month", "particularly", "on", "october", "or", "even", "during", "that", "period", "of", "time", "why", "do", "not", "they", "go", "to", "their", "attorney", "and", "say", "look", "there", "be", "just", "no", "way", "we", "can", "pay", "it"]]}, {"text": "Why wait three months until the solicitor goes in and says I want an order to revoke your probation?", "start": 3508.126, "stop": 3513.963, "duration": 5.84, "cleanText": [["why", "wait", "three", "month", "until", "the", "solicitor", "go", "in", "and", "say", "i", "want", "an", "order", "to", "revoke", "your", "probation"]]}, {"text": "Where is the good faith effort on their part?", "start": 3513.963, "stop": 3520.384, "duration": 6.42, "cleanText": [["where", "be", "the", "good", "faith", "effort", "on", "their", "part"]]}, {"text": "And I think that's fundamental.", "start": 3520.384, "stop": 3521.952, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "think", "that", "be", "fundamental"]]}, {"text": "I think we need to reach that issue and I think in reaching it, we would hope that the Court would say that the trial judge in this case did not abuse his discretion.", "start": 3521.952, "stop": 3535.077, "duration": 13.13, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "we", "need", "to", "reach", "that", "issue", "and", "i", "think", "in", "reach", "it", "we", "would", "hope", "that", "the", "court", "would", "say", "that", "the", "trial", "judge", "in", "this", "case", "do", "not", "abuse", "his", "discretion"]]}, {"text": "And we thank you for that.", "start": 3535.077, "stop": 3537.579, "duration": 2.5, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "thank", "you", "for", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, gentlemen.", "start": 3537.579, "stop": 3538.362, "duration": 0.78, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "gentleman"]]}, {"text": "The case is submitted.", "start": 3538.362, "stop": 3539.345, "duration": 0.98, "cleanText": [["the", "case", "be", "submit"]]}]}]}], "decidedBy": "Burger Court", "arguedOn": "Nov 4, 1980", "petitioner": "Wood", "respondent": "Georgia", "docket": "79-6027", "citation": "450US261(1981)", "justiaLink": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/450/261", "lowerCourt": "State appellate court", "grantedOn": "", "decidedOn": "Mar 4, 1981"}